text: cieszę się, że został złapany człowiek, który napadł na studentkę z łodzi. mam też nadzieję, że dostanie sprawiedliwy wyrok, a sprawa nie zostanie potraktowana poblazliwie (jak czesto ma to miejsce w tego typu sprawach). tak sobie myślę, czy ta sytuacja miałaby takie zakończenie gdyby dziewczyna nie opublikowala swojej historii w social mediach. do czego muszą uciekać się ofiary by zostać zauważone i żeby zaczęto traktować je poważnie. do upubliczniania tego co powoduje ich ból, cierpienie i wstyd. bo ofiary już w trakcie przesłuchań traktowane są w sposób straszny, zadawane są pytania, które nie mają związku ze sprawą, nierzadko pod swoim adresem słyszą komentarze "mogła pani tam nie łazić". ofiary przestępstw na tle seksualnym często bardziej wstydzą się tego co zaszło aniżeli sam sprawca. kiedyś oglądałam pewien serial "sons of anarchy" - jedna z bohaterek została zgwałcona i nie przejmowała się tym co zaszło. martwiła się tym, że jej mąż nie będzie już jej chciał, ze po gwalcie będzie dla niego brudna, dotknięta. żyjemy niestety w świecie, w którym kobiety od początku startują z gorszej pozycji.

text:
dear mom of boys,⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
just a friendly reminder that now is the time to raise kind men 🙏🏾🙌🏾⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i am asking you to please talk to your sons about women’s rights, about kindness, about boundaries and limits, teach them to not put up with disrespectful “jokes” about women 🤦🏾‍♀️⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i just heard my 4yo call his nanny “fat” 🤦🏾‍♀️ and even though it may have seemed innocent, it was an opportunity to speak up as a mother, as a woman and as an employer. teach your boys that it isn’t their place to comment on a woman’s body. because of you, they will grow up to take notice of a woman’s smart brain, witty humor or kind heart 💕🥰⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
keep holding your boys responsible for their actions and the outcomes. keep teaching them to keep their hands to themselves. to not resort to violence, to use their words. boys will not be boys! boys will be kind!⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i am asking you to start this now - when they are still little boys; before they get a chance to get their answers online, or from the wrong people. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
let’s raise a generation of men who will read about the #metoo movement in the history books and shake their heads in disbelief.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
dear m.o.b, stay the course 🙌🏾✊🏽✊🏽⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
i didn’t expect to be here right now. honesty, i thought i would be dead.

either from suicide or from obesity. i just didn’t expect “thriving” to be a possibility when i spent my whole life just trying to survive.

i was heavily bullied in school. rumours, fat jokes, pranks, you name it.

my past of being sexually molested at the age of 3 haunted me. i was raped at 14 by a classmate. the loss of my first child due to my health left me feeling like a failure.

i remember in one of my darkest moments, when the pain was too much, the depression was deep, i planned my suicide.

i put on a happy face and pretended to be happy but the reality is, i was dying inside.

i felt so out of control that i thought my only way to escape out of how i was feeling was just to end it.

at over 300lb, i couldn’t stop binging on food. food for me was my alcohol and i needed it to keep me sane. it was my escape from reality and it was going to kill me one way or another.

i saw no way out. i was ready to leave this world.

but i couldn’t. see, there was this one thing that kept me here.

a tiny human, who shared my body with me for 9 months. a beautiful little boy who gave me unconditional love.

i struggled with post partum depression, and what most moms don’t admit to, is having thoughts of suicide. all my past trauma magnified by 1000 with ppd.

i battled with it for 3 years after my son was born, and i felt again like a failure. i just didn’t feel like i could be the mother he needed. i was damaged.

but... one beautiful spring day, i was sent a very loud message from the universe that it was time to take care of myself and learn to love myself just as much as he loved me.

that day, he ran from me at the park while we were playing, and my heavy frame was unable to catch up with him. he bolted out the gates and into the street. a black mazda halted inches from his tiny blonde head.

in that moment, i woke up. i had so much love around me and because i only focused on the pain, i almost missed out on the best part of my life.

to this day, he is my driving force to love my life as happy and healthy as i can be. i want to show him just how much of a survivor his mama is. ❤

text:
nobel′in sahibini belirleyen akademide istifa | avrupa | dw
#nobel #saradanius #taciz
 kadınlara yönelik tacizleri ortaya çıkan #metoo kampanyası nobel edebiyat ödülleri'nin kime verileceğini belirleyen i̇sveç akademisi'nde bir istifaya daha neden oldu. akademinin eski daimi genel sekreteri sara danius görevi bıraktığını resmi olarak açıkladı. danius, yayınladığı mesajında, "koltuğumu bırakma kararı aldım. bu görev bir onurdu" dedi. 56 yaşındaki danius, açıklamasında kararına ilişkin gerekçe sunmadı. stokholm üniversitesi'nde akademisyen olan danius, 2013 yılında akademiye katılmıştı. geçtiğimiz yıl görevi bırakan danius, akademinin ilk kadın daimi sekreteriydi. sara danius i̇stifanın arkasında nisan 2018'de akademiyi sarsan cinsel taciz ve sızıntı skandalı yatıyor. akademinin üyeleri arasında yer alan katarina frostenson'un eşi claude arnault, genç bir kadına tecavüz etmekten suçlu bulunmuştu. i̇sveç akademisi, edebiyat çevrelerinde oldukça etkili bir foruma sahip olan arnault'u maddi olarak destekliyordu. i̇ki yıl hapis cezasına mahkum edilen jean-claude arnault'un, nobel ödülü'nü kazananların ismini kamuoyuna sızdırdığı da iddia edilmişti. skandal, fronstenson'un istifa etmesine neden olmuştu. danius da akademiyi sarsan krizin yönetimi konusunda eleştiri oklarının hedefi olmuştu.  danius'un istifası sonrası i̇sveç akademisi'nin daimi sekreteri anders olsson tarafından yapılan açıklamada, boşalan koltukların kadınlar tarafından doldurulacağı belirtildi. i̇lerleyen yaşı nedeniyle görevi bırakmaya hazırlanan olsson, "akademide kadın ve erkek dengesini korumak önemli" dedi. i̇sveç akademisini sarsan skandal nedeniyle geçtiğimiz yıl nobel edebiyat ödülleri verilmemişti. bu yıl iki ödül birden verilecek. dpa,afp/ns,öa © deutsche welle türkçe  haber kaynağı

 kadınlara yönelik tacizleri ortaya çıkan #metoo kampanyası nobel edebiyat ödülleri'nin kime verileceğini belirleyen i̇sveç akademisi'nde bir istifaya daha neden oldu. akademinin eski daimi genel sekreteri sara danius görevi bıraktığını resmi olarak açıkladı. danius, yayınladığı mesajında, "koltuğumu bırakma kararı aldım. bu görev bir onurdu" dedi. 56 yaşındaki danius, açıklamasında kararına ilişkin gerekçe sunmadı. stokholm üniversitesi'nde akademisyen olan danius, 2013 yılında akademiye katılmıştı. geçtiğimiz yıl görevi bırakan danius, akademinin ilk kadın daimi sekreteriydi. sara danius i̇stifanın arkasında nisan 2018'de akademiyi sarsan cinsel taciz ve sızıntı skandalı yatıyor. akademinin üyeleri arasında yer alan katarina frostenson'un eşi claude arnault, genç bir kadına tecavüz etmekten suçlu bulunmuştu. i̇sveç akademisi, edebiyat çevrelerinde oldukça etkili bir foruma sahip olan arnault'u maddi olarak destekliyordu. i̇ki yıl hapis cezasına mahkum edilen jean-claude arnault'un, nobel ödülü'nü kazaların ismini kamuoyuna sızdırdığı da iddia edilmişti. skandal, fronstenson'un istifa etmesine neden olmuştu. danius da akademiyi sarsan krizin yönetimi konusunda eleştiri oklarının hedefi olmuştu.  danius'un istifası sonrası i̇sveç akademisi'nin daimi sekreteri anders olsson tarafından yapılan açıklamada, boşalan koltukların kadınlar tarafından doldurulacağı belirtildi. i̇lerleyen yaşı nedeniyle görevi bırakmaya hazırla olsson, "akademide kadın ve erkek dengesini korumak önemli" dedi. i̇sveç akademisini sarsan skandal nedeniyle geçtiğimiz yıl nobel edebiyat ödülleri verilmemişti. bu yıl iki ödül birden verilecek. dpa,afp/ns,öa © deutsche welle türkçe  haber kaynağı

text:
when you raise your voice be prepared to be victim blamed and laughed upon.
be prepared to loose all those people whom you thought are your frnds, be prepared to be left alone in the darkness,be prepared to be laughed at and talk about and be prepared to be a survivor. if you can conquer this then you can conquer anything in life.
to all the survivor and victims,never let anyone to dim your lite or allow yourself to question your character..the one who speaks bad about you is the reflection of who they are and not who you are. similar way the one who caused this to you is the reflection of who they are and not who you are. do not expect justice from humans for they are not superior to god. when god gives justice then he will give it through numerous ways and one of the way is that you survived. #metoo #nomore

text:
black herstory month: tarana burke- 
born september 12, 1973 - born and raised in the bronx, ny. the lifelong community organizer and grassroots activist turned her experience as a survivor of sexual violence into a means of helping other women by founding the me too movement in 2006—a full decade before the #metoo hashtag went viral last fall as an expression of women’s experiences with sexual harassment and assault. the movement was an outgrowth of just be inc., the organization she started that same year to empower young women of color. ✨✨✨✨ “get up. stand up. speak up. do something.” - tarana burke •
•
•

text:
i open my heart 
not with carelessness,
but with humility. 
so you can read 
the foreign language 
that is trapped inside my chest.
that i cannot comprehend myself,
so that you can tell me 
what i truly feel,
because this foreign language 
is becoming too difficult 
to carry
myself.
-
an absolutely gorgeous portrait in oils by @kayknightley
-

text:
bueno, la verdad es que esta mañana me desperté con publicar algo antes de las 2 de la mañana, pero mi plan no era difundir lo siguiente que les voy a decur. 
este es un tema serio y de actualidad el cual todxs estamos involucrados de alguna manera y mi intervención no es provoca miedo,  al contrario, es previniendo que algo malo les pase.... como cada mañana,  revisó mis redes sociales y veo el grupo que tengo en conjunto con mis amigas.  no le tomó importancia, pero luego veo las historias de mi cuenta personal y no me lo podía creer. 
cómo es posible que allá tanta basura en el mundo?  cómo es posible que allá chicas que salgan a la calle con miedo de no volver? 
tengo una amiga que,  revisando los mensajes en el grupo dice que tiene miedo de ir a su clase de danza.  y eso, para mi, fue el colmo de males. 
ya no más. por eso público esto, aquí y ahora.  no sé o si me van a pescar,  o no. pero, por favor,  seas chico o chica, o quien sea que este leyendo esto en este instante,  cuídate. ~alaska

text: over the past few years, we have all seen the phrase “#metoo” all over the media. on wednesday, march 6 from 1:00-3:20, the gwrf will dig deeper into this topic in the screening and conversation panel, “me too is everywhere.” the first hour will be spent screening the emmy nominated documentary “rape in the fields.” in the second hour, investigative reporters will discuss the sexual violence and intimidation that is endured by some of the most vulnerable working women. please join us in the mclaren complex at usf if you’d like to learn more and see a different side of the #metoo movement.  #gwrf2019

text:
i’m happy to announce we are officially accepting members to rise, a 10-week therapeutic group for women-identified survivors of sexual trauma. during rise, members will connect with others who have had similar experiences, engage in healing discussions that explore the impact of trauma, & build neuroscience-based coping skills necessary to thrive in today’s world. upon completion, members will have a customized wellness plan that they may carry into daily life with a newfound sense of strength, control, & resiliency.
•
•
to maintain a safe & intimate group, we are only able to welcome a small number of women each round. if you are interested in scheduling a complimentary 30-minute phone consultation to assess if this is the right group for you, please call us at 626.524.5525 or email us at info@drtruitt.com!

text:

“why i need the era:

text:
for all the times i’ve said no, that have been brushed away, ignored.. not taken seriously.. anger bubbles.. why wasn’t i heard? •
an underlying confusion: should i have been louder, clearer, more determined?
•
it takes two for sure, and at some point it just seems easier to give in than be demanding.. i mean.. how many times do i have to say it? do you not think i know what i want and don’t?!
•
amidst that there is shame, doubt, and a questioning.. does it really mean anything? does it matter? is it all silliness..
•
if i were speaking to another it would be very clear.. •
no means no..
•
yet, being personally involved, doubt bubbles.. it can seem so small, so insignificant.. and at the same time it hurts so deep.. some sort of betrayal to the self..
•

text:
#1
seule

seule quand tous ceux qui devraient être derrière toi t’enfoncent et disent que c’est de ta faute.
seule face à une justice qui te considère comme un suspect et non comme une victime.
seule face aux médecins, aux psychiatres, qui dissèquent tes séquelles et te rappellent à quel point ça t’a marquée.
seule face à tes amis qui ont du mal à admettre que le mec qu’ils connaissent est un violeur.
seule face à lui qui rôde autour de toi comme une ombre maléfique, quelqu’un dont tu dois te méfier en permanence. lui qui revient même en rêve te faire revivre ce qu’il t’a fait subir.
seule face aux gars de ton âge devant lesquels tu ne peux t’empêcher de te dire que dans le secret d’une alcôve, ils ont peut-être été eux aussi des violeurs.
seule face aux petites filles dont tu as la charge, quand tu crains que le viol soit aussi leur lot à elle aussi.
seule face à la foule insouciante de ceux devant qui tu dois être joyeuse et te conduire comme si tu avais une vie normale.
seule face à tes angoisses, tes doutes, ta haine, ton envie de mourir
seule face à la culture du viol

#metoo #rapevictim #noustoutes #saynotorapeculture

text:
הרבה דברים אמרה מאיה בוסקילה בראיון לעיתון לאישה, אך נבחרה אמירה אחת בלבד על ידי המערכת לתמצות דבריה, אשר מוכיחה את הצהרתה כ'לא פמיניסטית'. הכתבה, מהותה כביכול 'כתבת פרגון לכוכבת שחזרה לזרוח', אך לצערנו לא מוציאה את בוסקילה באור חיובי כלל, לאור המשפט שנבחר לייצוגה. 
מאיה, התמודדה ועודנה עם אתגרים שונים בהם נתקלות אמהות חד הוריות. למראית עין, ולפי הכתבה, עוברת את המשוכות בהצלחה ומנהלת חיים אימהיים לצד חזרה לקריירה כזמרת. היא מציינת את השינוי שחלחל בתודעה, הן הכללית הן שלה עצמה לנושא ההטרדות המיניות וקמפיין #metoo. אם כן אז מדוע כעיתון להיתפס לאמירה אחת שטחית? דעותיה ובחירותיה הרומנטיות של הזמרת, אינן העניין - אך כאשר מדובר באישה ידוענית, מהותה מצטמצמת לרכילויות צהובות, ולא להישגיה הראויים לשבח, גם בראיון מסוג זה. מי כמונו יודעות שדברים הנאמרים לעתים מוצאים מהקשר, ובמקרה הנוכחי, אפילו מבודדים ממנו.
מה יותר מציג עוצמה נשית מאשר אישה הבוחרת בדרך לחיות את חייה, לגדל את בנה לפי מה שהיא מאמינה, לצד ניהול קריירה ובחירה מקצועית נטולת אגו, כזמרת עם עבר מרשים להתמודד בתכנית אליה מגיעים זמרים מכל הקשת המקצועית, בכדי לייצג את ישראל באירוויזיון. 
אז מאיה, דעותיך ובחירותיך בנוגע להשתתפות וניהול משק הבית שלך וההשפעה על החשק המיני שלך, כל אלה באמת שלך. אך בבקשה, אל תצהירי על עצמך שאינך פמיניסטית, כאישה החזקה והעצמאית שאת. (למרות שאנחנו מציעות לך בחום להתחלק עם בן זוגך במשימות הבית, זה הרבה יותר נוח)
name: Slut Walk JLM

stop_filter_tweet: הרבה דברים אמרה מאיה בוסקילה בראיון לעיתון לאישה , אך נבחרה אמירה אחת בלבד על ידי המערכת לתמצות דבריה , אשר מוכיחה את הצהרתה כ'לא פמיניסטית ' . הכתבה , מהותה כביכול 'כתבת פרגון לכוכבת שחזרה לזרוח ' , אך לצערנו לא מוציאה את בוסקילה באור חיובי כלל , לאור המשפט שנבחר לייצוגה . מאיה , התמודדה ועודנה עם אתגרים שונים בהם נתקלות אמהות חד הוריות . למראית עין , ולפי הכתבה , עוברת את המשוכות בהצלחה ומנהלת חיים אימהיים לצד חזרה לקריירה כזמרת . היא מציינת את השינוי שחלחל בתודעה , הן הכללית הן שלה עצמה לנושא ההטרדות המיניות וקמפיין אם כן אז מדוע כעיתון להיתפס לאמירה אחת שטחית ? דעותיה ובחירותיה הרומנטיות של הזמרת , אינן העניין - אך כאשר מדובר באישה ידוענית , מהותה מצטמצמת לרכילויות צהובות , ולא להישגיה הראויים לשבח , גם בראיון מסוג זה . מי כמונו יודעות שדברים הנאמרים לעתים מוצאים מהקשר , ובמקרה הנוכחי , אפילו מבודדים ממנו . מה יותר מציג עוצמה נשית מאשר אישה הבוחרת בדרך לחיות את חייה , לגדל את בנה לפי מה שהיא מאמינה , לצד ניהול קריירה ובחירה מקצועית נטולת אגו , כזמרת עם עבר מרשים להתמודד בתכנית אליה מגיעים זמרים מכל הקשת המקצועית , בכדי לייצג את ישראל באירוויזיון . אז מאיה , דעותיך ובחירותיך בנוגע להשתתפות וניהול משק הבית שלך וההשפעה על החשק המיני שלך , כל אלה באמת שלך . אך בבקשה , אל תצהירי על עצמך שאינך פמיניסטית , כאישה החזקה והעצמאית שאת . ( למרות שאנחנו מציעות לך בחום להתחלק עם בן זוגך במשימות הבית , זה הרבה יותר נוח )

text:
my final piece for the 'vessel' ceramics project on my art and design course. i had loads of fun making this, and researching it and all the different ideas behind it.
the mug has "smash the patriarchy" stamped on it, there are pieces referring to various movements that i have been inspired by and that j think have done a lot for women. i also added in a cotton placenta with a white tampon style string on the inside of the cup. i find it ironic that the placenta is what feeds and keeps us all thriving before we are born yet men are disgusted by it and all the "stuff" that makes us females. they don't understand that they're not here without us! 
#smashthepatriarchy #feminist #stronggirlsclub #repeal #metoo #timesup #nastywoman 
#artanddesign #carlislecollege

text: whether you report to cops or not, this is important.  i know our story has inspired others to rally and seek justice, and others’ stories have done the same for us.  you matter and you are still you. the only one who should feel shame and guilt and trauma is the rapist.  it’s the rapist who should know that he’s damaged, not you. don’t ever believe you are.  you are always you.  the hurt and pain you may feel is not yours to carry, it should be given back to the monster who tried to infect you with it. sharing your story helps you and helps others who are going through the same thing.  you’re stronger than you think you are.  #outtherapists #limpdickrapist #coerciverapeisrape #corestrategycorp #vonkarmantowers #rape #youarestrong #metoo #stoprape #survivor

text:
have you tried the exercise thing, but fell off one too many times?
or 
maybe you have been on the ups and downs of the yo yo dieting?

maybe food & exercise is your control?
maybe its your out of control?

where ever you may find yourself, can you honestly say you have a good healthy handle on your health?

when you look in the mirror do you criticize yourself and hate what you seen?

well, maybe its not a diet and exercise problem after all.

what if it goes way deeper?

i am bundling my entire system together for you to find true health, healing, and wholeness in a fresh new way!

yes there is a workout program, 
but more importantly, we are going to dive into 
who you are, and how to approach health (yes food & fitness) gods way! 
it's time to cut the yo yo sting, the comparison string, the not good enough string, the doubting string, the excuses string.

lets learn how to truly honor our bodies, the way god calls us to, and fall in love with doing it!

text: es kommt alles wieder, was nicht bis zum ende gelitten und gelöst wird [hermann hesse] ⚫️ ich glaube, an dem zitat ist etwas wahres dran. sicher gibt es gründe, weshalb wir menschen verdrängen, dieser abwehrmechanismus ist mitunter überlebenswichtig. ich denke aber, dass uns alles irgendwann wieder einholt. das muss nicht bewusst sein, auch körperlich kann viel auf eine kranke seele hindeuten. auch mein körper zeigt symptome. er kann nicht ewig kompensieren, was meine seele trauern lässt. ich arbeite daran. und auch, wenn es saumäßig anstrengend ist, auch, wenn ich jeden dienstag voller unlust bei meiner therapeutin aufschlage, auch, wenn es mir danach fast immer schlecht geht und meine gedanken aufgewühlt sind - es muss sein. diese arbeit bin ich mir selbst schuldig. meine seele und mein körper haben es verdient, gesund leben zu dürfen. auch eure seelen, auch eure körper haben das verdient. wenn ihr denkt, ihr braucht hilfe - holt sie euch. es ist ein zeichen von stärke, sich diese not einzugestehen. oft reicht auch schon ein einzelnes gutes gespräch mit einem neutralen menschen. oft nicht. auch das ist okay! hinfallen ist keine schande - man muss nur wieder aufstehen 🙏 #trauma#ptbs#metoo#notanobject#mentalillness#mentalhealthawareness#health#healthy#mind#quote#model#fotoshooting#fotografie#blonde#thisisnotconsent

text:
victimisation- level 1 of the pyramid refers to things that people generally find acceptable, harmless, easier to ignore or fail to see how it plays into rape culture. rape culture starts with normalisation.
degradation- level 2  of the pyramid refers to issues that threaten the dignity of victims and causes violation and lack of respect.
removal of autonomy- level 3 of the pyramid refers to acts that take place when a victim is no longer in control, these acts infringe on their freedom. 
explicit violence- level 4 of the pyramid are acts of violence. 
#sexualviolence #rapeculture #metoo #womensupportingwomen #normalisation #toxicmasculinity #boyswillbeboys #victimblaming #sexualharrassment

morgenavond  is het zover! nog even ook wat praktische informatie voor de avond. inloop en last minute kaartverkoop start om 18.20 tot 18.50. wij hebben een strak programma en het wordt erg gewaardeerd om ruim op tijd aanwezig te zijn. om 19.00 stipt begint het programma. vanaf 19.15 gaan de deuren dicht.

het adres is: anna van buerenplein 301, 2595 dg, den haag

met ov: op 1 minuut loopafstand van den haag centraal.
loop naar het luc-gebouw (leiden university college), waar voor het gebouw iemand van de organisatie staat om de weg te wijzen.

programma in het kort:
opening
1e spreker: dr. karim
2e spreker: dr. van middelburg
interview met ervaringsdeskundige: mw. fatima
v&a
afsluiting
borrel bij de minglemush ------------------------------------------- the event is happening tomorrow evening! below you can find some practical information regarding the schedule, as well as the location.

registration and last-minute ticket sales start at 18:20 until 18:50. make sure you are on time, as this will ensure a smooth start of the event. the event starts at 19:00, and the doors close at 19:15.

the address is anna van buerenplein 301, 2595dg, the hague.

you can get there via public transport. once you get to the hague central station, walk out to the leiden university college building, where someone from montium will be waiting to show the way.

program in short:
opening
1st speaker: dr. karim
2nd speaker: dr. van middelburg
interview with an fgm-survivor: fatima
q&a
end of event
drinks at minglemush

text:
i never planned on posting this for all the reasons you’d think: i hate my body, i have stretch marks, i have cellulite everywhere, i will never have a thigh gap, etc. 
my wonderful and talented friend, @missfitphoto, took these for my 40th birthday last year... these were for me. this was also cathartic. i cried, but felt a wave of release come over me. 
written all over my body are just a fraction of the things he said to me. though i shared my story of abuse publicly, one of you shared my story with him. 
this is my reality. i might be “crazy” or “impulsive” or “fat” or “ugly” or “never look good in a bathing suit”, but i’m the one who is still healing. i have scars all over my heart and soul. y’all can say whatever you want... but it doesn’t take away from the fact that i went through what i went through. this is my life and my story. i won’t be apologizing anymore. i won’t live to impress anyone anymore. if you don’t believe me, i don’t care. this is my reality and i believe women. #unafraid

text:
in 2017, kenyette barnes and oronike odeleye founded the #muterkelly movement, pressuring the music industry to stop giving kelly the star treatment that had shielded him.
.
“it’s his money, it’s his wealth, it’s his notoriety, it’s all the connections that he has in the entertainment industry that make it hard for victims to successfully prosecute him,” odeleye told npr last year.
.
if the money dries up, their thinking went, he becomes more susceptible to justice.
because of #metoo, women are more likely to be believed, even the young black women who so often and so tragically are doubted, discounted and discarded as unimportant.
.
they are, more and more, understood to be the victims of “rape culture” — the disgusting but pervasive notion that sexual violence is something to be normalized and trivialized.
.
but some of what has happened was simply the power of how the story was told in the tv series, and whom it reached — a younger, more diverse audience than that of traditional journalism, told in text, whether on newsprint or online.
.
“the series was like a six-hour version of the new york magazine cover on bill cosby,” derogatis told me. “it had that kind of impact.”
.
he gives executive producer, dream hampton, much of the credit for that, and she in turn has credited his reporting. (rogatis’s book, “soulless: the case against r. kelly,” will be published in september; he has been reporting, most recently, for the new yorker magazine.)
.
because of the simple power of the storytelling, he said, “the women were the stars — they showed their pain.”
.
#muterkelly #rkelly #survivingrkelly #blackgirlsmatter #endrapeculture

text: i was very fortunate to attend the vh1 trailblazer honors awards and meet several trailblazers like nancy pelosi, tarana burke, margaret atwood, and ava duvernay. all the women i have mentioned have open pathways for other women. i especially got emotional when the #metoo movement founder and movement was mentioned because of the sexual harassment i have encountered in my life. the award show will be aired on march 8th, international women’s day. i’m in the table closest to the stage, you might get a glimpse of me looking in admiration of rita ora performing “soul survivor.” rita is my muse. #ritaora #strongwomen #womensupportwomen #womenempowerment

⁣

text:
podium marathon relais femmes 🏆 première place 🥇#carthagerace♥️♥️🇹🇳🇹🇳🇹🇳 très contente de partager cette course avec ma binôme amounn imen sassi magnifique expérience 💪💪🏃‍♀️🏃‍♀️ organisation, ambiance,parcours,ravito 🔝🔝🔝 bien sûr avec une  très jolie médaille ♥️🥇😍 et sûr tout les encouragements et l'humour des juges et des bénévoles bravooo bravooo 😍😘😘
#balancetoncoeur♥️, un rappel au fameux hashtag "#balancetonporc" ou encore le "#metoo". c'est un hashtag hommage aux agressions faites aux femmes dans le monde, mais aussi les agressions faites aux hommes. une manière pour montrer mon soutien en tant que femme à chaque personne victime d'une agression dans le monde. il ne faut pas oublier que rien qu'en 2015, près de 78% des victimes d'agressions sont des femmes dans le monde et 22% d'hommes. la tunisie n'est pas épargnée puisqu'il y a en moyenne 3 viols par jour recensés en 2018. #balancetoncoeur♥️ est un hashtag pour rappeler à chaque être humain qu'il n'est certainement pas seul et  qu'il faut toujours rester unis et solidaires car ensemble et main dans la main, on peut tout vaincre et on peut avancer. #kindness #ensemble
le sport a le pouvoir de nous réunir peu importe qui nous sommes, pendant quelques heures  on est égaux, réunis pour une même cause ( courir ensemble🏃‍♀️🏃‍♂️). c'est un moment de partage qui nous fait oublier  nos différences😍.
ouevrons tous ensemble à encourager ce sport noble la course à pied.. le symbole de dépassement de soit l'art de s'exprimer librement à travers son corps sa foie et sa volonté😊😉.. #banirleboycot🇹🇳 #carthagerace♥️♥️🇹🇳🇹🇳🇹🇳 #runningclubtunis #lifestyle #love #running

text:
ajay sathyan is a survivor of child abuse, rape, suicide attempt and police brutality, who fled india to protect his dignity and life. ajay's life has been a constant battle to survive violence and brutality instigated by patriarchal standards. now, in europe ajay's faced with toxic whiteness along with regressive patriarchal systems. through his many attempts to secour help (fearing suicide), ajay was forced to live with disappointment and blame. now, ajay has taken the mantle to express his pain, angst, fear, disappointment, depression, wit, critique and maybe humor through art. also, ajay is on the verge of completing an autobiography and hopefully, publish few works of fiction later.

( my mom, used to pronounce, it like that, she was pro-british ) kashmir, a lovely place.... but, can't go there.... too much of trouble, all around..... so, its good for us, only in the hindi movies.... otherwise, we cannot enjoy, kashmir's #beauty..... .
.
so, that's that..... .
.

text:
lo han vuelto a hacer, @femenspain reivindica los derechos de las mujeres dando voz al feminismo de nuestro país. 
los votos más conservadores pueden meter a pablo casado, albert rivera o santiago abascal en el parlamento pero no vamos a permitir que entren a mandar en nuestros úteros. 
llevamos dejando claro mucho tiempo que sobre nuestro cuerpo decidimos nosotras, estamos cansadas de que dirigentes machistas opinen sobre lo que debemos hacer cómo mujeres. no señores, no vamos a permitir que retrocedamos a la ley del aborto de 1985 para que las ricas vuelvan a abortar en londres y las pobres mueran en la clandestinidad. 
el aborto legal, seguro y gratuito es un avance social, no vamos a volver atrás.
cada vez estoy más segura. la revolución será feminista o no será. 
fotografía de @lauracvela

text: getting in front of the camera gives me the worst anxiety. when i was 3 years old a man used me for his own purposes. he made me youth-less. i was 12 years old before telling my mother because of threats he made to me. when i told her she took me to the church and the church leaders prayed over me. that was the end of it. he is still out there. he has social media. i don’t want him to see me. i don’t know what to do. i have to get passed this. my story will help so many. does anyone have any advice. i can’t let this affect me anymore. he has controlled so much of my life, he can’t take this from me too. #metoo

text:
***trigger warning: sexual assault/rape

here’s the logo design created by my significant other @deleonjullian for dead girl rising, or in its abbreviated form dgr. thanks baby! love you! ❤️it’s placed over some headlines that have served as inspiration when writing my music. i’m a survivor of childhood sexual abuse. when i see these types of headlines, it makes me upset, sad, angry. it reminds me of some of my negative experiences. this is why i put a trigger warning at the top, because i know how triggering these headlines can be in stirring up memories, and emotions. while researching articles for this, my bf and i got so sad reading about it. if you’re someone whose also experienced sexual abuse traumas, know that you are not alone, there are so many people going through the same things. the sadness, the guilt, the thoughts of suicide, feeling dirty. healing is possible! hold on, you’ll build resilience, you’ll keep going! you will do great things! if you are down today, you can rise again tomorrow! #metoo #endsexualviolence #endsexualabuse #believeher #rise #torontomusician #pianorock #feminist #womensrights #womensrightsarehumanrights #endviolenceagainstwomen #endviolenceagainstsexworkers #endviolenceagainstwomenandgirls #feminism #riotgrrrl #riotgrrrls #experimentalrock #gothicpiano

text:
meet our speakers: anjela ford-glueckert first attended a no more national anti-violence summit back in 2017.  now anjela is excited to present at this year’s summit and share her wisdom, as well as her personal experience about her heart-language asl (american sign language), and share how you can integrate a more welcoming deaf presence into your community and agency events.

attend this inspiring workshop by registering at nomoresummit.org

read more about anjela ford-glueckert
anjela is the blissful mama and owner/ceo of anjelabundance. anjela believes the world is a better place when mamas are well-rested, nourished, calm, and infinitely more. to help other mamas remember the “me before mama”, anjela has embarked on a quest to get mothers to slow down. she uses her years of facilitation and teaching to lead overwhelmed mamas on their own path back to the woman in their mirror. 
#nomoresummit #endthebacklog #iamevidence #nomoreexcuses #nomoreweek #nwcave #metoo #timesup #stoptheviolence #stopthehate #wasaysnomore

text:
before that nerve-wrecking moment the only form in which blood existed for her 6 year old self was in her veins and it could only ooze out when she would get a paper-cut or would injure her finger with scissors. she would cry in panic each time she'd injure herself for the sight of blood horrified her. 
it was on a life-changing winter evening when she discovered a new outlet of blood flow in her body. although the outlet was new, she could still identify with the excruciating pain that paved way for blood flow from her 'forbidden part', the only senstation that became a bridge for her to remain consciously in touch with her former self. however, this time she didn't cry or crib. perhaps her pain had overpowered her emotions? this time a familiar hand had covered her face, a hand that would reward her with candies if she maintained silence. the coarse voice belonging to the familiar hand reassured her that she would get candies. it reiterated the fact that she's a good girl and that it should remain a secret. 
his secret still remains. in the form of a burden that she's bearing on her body, mind and soul. the familiar hand stained with her virgin blood suffocates her as it still covers her mouth. however, over these 16 years the familiar hand has taken the place of her conscious drenched in sorrow and smothered in the memory of the most excruciating abdominal pain she had ever endured in all these years. the hand is that of a conscious that trembles at the thought of surfacing her grief and leads her to collapsing, time and again. however, the secret remains. virgin blood of her 6 year old self smothered on her face, protects the secret of that beast and will continue doing so for all times to come. -to those silent sufferers.

text:
do not touch her:
a free-spirited girl, very liberal, consumed in her bravado. 
you thought you could touch her, and she'd be okay with it. 
she is so comfortable in her body, she is pleased with it. she wouldn't mind if you get comfortable with it too, right?

she shows it off, like an armour, an armour can be played with, armour is not skin, it can belong to anyone. even you, right? 
wrong! don't touch it, you will burn her. she is not to be held.
 she is not to be misunderstood. 
her freedom is not an open invitation or call of desperation. it is her right! 
just let her be. don't touch her.

text:
this is something i never talk about publicly, and likely never will again. but while i want to keep some parts of my life private, i decided i should share something, to remove any stigma or shame of this diagnosis and to remind myself that i am a patient too. this month, i am celebrating a particular anniversary of being cancer free myself. 
years ago, i was diagnosed with a very early stage of a very lethal cancer. thankfully it was found early and only required surgery to remove it. i was extremely fortunate not to need any chemotherapy or radiation, or any other treatments. while mind-numbing at the time, i talked to my siblings and parents, to make sure they were evaluated as well, and went forward with the procedure. yet my scar reminds me that i am mortal, and that maybe worrying over something silly just isn't worth the breath in my lungs.

there is always a small voice in the back of my mind that reminds me it could return any day. i get screened for recurrence, and am vigilant for signs and symptoms. if it truly returned, i would not last a year. but i choose not to think like that, i simply can't. instead of focusing on my mortality, i choose to make every attempt to live in the moment and focus on what it means to live - and yes, that means giving in to some disagreements or particular demands from my kids. (i mean, who cares if they have another spoonful of nutella?? there must be some protein in there....) as my husband says, this won't be the hill i die on. and he's right. my hill is a long way away.
name: Niamey Wilson, MD, FACS

text:

text:
the 3 essential p of life: passion, persistence, perseverance. .
.
.
this picture was taken on november 08th, 2016, in nanjing, china. my poster was presented as indonesia's only representative on 2016 international pharmacy forum by fip x china pharmaceutical university.
.
.
.
i'll tell you the truth; it's always bizzare even to me, about my whole journey as a pharmacy student. how did i finished my journey is as much mysterious as how i was there at the first place.
.
.
often people come to me; "but you did achieve here and there, this and that"
.
.
maybe, it was because i always believe that i have to excell my capacities, to finish what has been started (this is also often the reason why i received many snickers, or being worried too much. maybe) .
.
.
so here i am today, in early 2019, staring at the old pictures of achieving the impossible. i'm sitting here, while holding to pixar studio and oscar statues photos, things that mattered. have i poured the 3 essential p these far, toward it? i guess i haven't. am i afraid? yes. am i competitive? honestly, yes. .
.
but will i give up? no. because comparing can never bring me anywhere. so, even if i'm afraid, bring it on! i'm ready, and i will always be prepared. .
.
#byl #thechroniclesofl #ltravellouge #china #nanjing #passion #persistence #perseverance #love #instagood #instapic #leanit #pictures #happiness #travelling #metoo

text:
-
#2019一百個書與非書的閱讀／017
〈#metoo will not survive unless we recognize toxic femininity〉meghan daum
-
「如果你曾把自己的惡行惡狀怪到月經頭上，請舉手。如果你曾在某些令人不愉快的家務（例如清老鼠屍體）面前假裝無助，請舉手。」
-
作者在文章開頭做了一連串像這這樣的調查。而文章主訴女人應該正視自己選擇性利用陰柔氣質獲取利益的問題。作者認為，唯有認清這個事實，metoo運動才有未來。

摁，聽到女人叫女人不要女性自助餐實在是件很新奇／詭異的事。

我以為女性主義就是要破除這些性別框架，破除「人家女生耶」背後暗藏的歧視與「男陽剛，女陰柔」陳腐至極的性別角色印象。
-
搭配閱讀
📖 《we should all be feminist 》chimamanda ngozi adichie
-

a lawsuit alleging sexually predatory behavior is grabbing donald trump by the toupee. ----------------------------------------- .

text: whether you realize it or not, recovery from addiction is a revolutionary act in the truest sense. it is a radical re-ordering of self. first is the emotionally violent overthrow of the old way, followed by a period of excitement and newness. lastly comes the difficult work of normalizing the new way. keep in mind that your new boundaries, views, attitudes, and beliefs can cause conflict with those who may welcome your sobriety, but be threatened by your recovery. we occupy a fixed position the minds of some and the further we go in recovery the more we challenge a dynamic that has suited them more than it has suited us. remain alert, tread lightly and arm yourself with kindness, but always be prepared for the ambush, to defend yourself against those who repeatedly say they are proud of you, yet always seem to find a reason to deny, belittle or otherwise punish you. most people are kind and do genuinely care, but kindness is also a veil behind which those who wish to harm you will hide in plain sight. there are those who will prey on people in early recovery. as radical feminism and whisper networks become more entrenched, men especially must be vigilant when welcoming unfamiliar females into their lives because far more than your recovery is at stake. #recoverywarrior #recoveryrevolution #soberlifestyle #metoo #radicalfeminism #staystrong #knowledgeisgrowth #calumnias #existentialism #readbooks #autodidactism #selfcare #besafe #rudeboys

text: los números dicen que la ceremonia número 91 de los premios de la academia subió un 11,5 % con relación al año anterior, que fue un año de números bajos. en mucho ha debido influir la presencia de lady gaga, queen y black panther. no tanto así, la ausencia de un maestro de ceremonias que dirigiera una velada errática -y sorporifera-, cuyas mayores crisis este año pasaron por prescindir de kevin hart como animador y por rectificar su decisión de entregar determinadas estatuillas durante los comerciales. superados ambos entuertos, el guion dio resultado. la academia ha tomado nota de las crisis de otros años y en silencio la industria ha orientado sus apuestas, nominaciones, premios y ceremonia. también ha favorecido al cine más popular por encima de otro artísticamente más celebrado pero menos taquillero. se ha notado, y mucho. los votantes también han tomado nota. pero tras el #oscarsowhite , el #metoo y el discurso de los #dreamers hollywood ha cambiado para que todo siga igual. la industria ha dado batalla y plantado cara a @netflix también ha consolidado su mirada premiando a un film clásico a la manera de hollywood. los ecos de driving miss daisy (1989) de bruce beresford han acompañado al film de farrelly, que ha sabido empatizar con el espectador. su película, por la que no fue nominado como director (al igual que beresford), es un regalo de buenas intenciones y en el futuro cercano uno de los films que las cadenas de tv programaran con frecuencia en navidad. bien actuado y bien escrito, el film no defrauda en su forma. aunque quizás no supere lecturas más relacionadas con el fondo. eso sí, ha triunfado allí donde the help y hidden figures fallaron. ya lo predecían las estadísticas. green book ganó en el profético festival de cine de toronto y también entre los premios de los productores, dos galardones que suelen estar asociados al triunfo en los óscar y este año no ha sido diferente. en el universo de lo políticamente correcto y la lapidacion digital, hollywood parece haber encontrado el tono y mimetizarlo con el suyo propio. #oscars #oscars2019 #hollywood

text:
este jueves 28 estaré leyendo poemas nuevos y sacando a la luz cómo se escribe siendo mujer joven (ya no tanto) en este momento. lo haré en una mesa redonda con mujeres que son fuertes y lo saben (qué mujer no lo es) y después habrá micro abierto. os contaré también cómo llevamos el proceso de construcción del retrato audiovisual de leopoldo de luis y la poesía de posguerra. cómo concibo un documental poético y cómo voy a tratar la #videopoesía.

hemos vivido muchos cambios en los últimos años. cuando escribí el poema que inspiró años más tarde #nosomosmusassomosartistas yo me consideraba una superviviente, aunque seguía cayendo en la víctima. ahora me considero una protectora. será la edad pero #metoo y si tocas a una, no voy a poner otra vez la otra mejilla. esto es lo que ahora me nace, proteger a todas las que comienzan el camino y eso que sé que aún no he dado ni dos pasos. queda mucho por andar y sin embargo muchas cosas puedo decir, he vivido y debería contar. mi silencio no me protegerá y tampoco ellos.

yo decía así y creía que ya estaba, que el escudo invisible y sacar corazón a la superficie, era suficiente:

razones por las que nunca seré una musa

1. no voy a morir joven. voy a marchitarme y no va a ser agradable, como una rosa destronada en una batucada de bueyes furiosos en estampida.

2. no voy a posar, mientras tus dedos me dibujan y me escorzan, felizmente. no voy a inspirarte ningún retrato eterno.

3. ya no estoy en matrix. no soy un holograma de belleza. ni se te ocurra decir que mi fuerza está en mi vientre o que soy el trampolín a la fama que te plancho o que te lavo.

4. yo soy la poeta y no la musa. la que muere mil veces en un lecho de colibríes negros y se desnuda ante el esqueleto de los fantasmas de su propia guerra.

5. fumo en cachimba el humo de amapola de tu piel vacía, eres tú mi dorian grey, eres tú mi reflejo roto y yo no puedo ser tu musa porque eres tú mi hermes, mi pluma seca, partitura y violonchelo, la cortina del telón que lo domina todo

6. yo soy la que sale a rasgarse en esta escena y aunque es mía la sangre de tus botas, mío es el desfiladero del dolor y también, la gloria.

#poetas #poemas #feminismo #feministas

text:
@soulmori sent me some rough sketches for valkyrie yesterday! having such a nice time collaborating with her. given the topic of the book i didn’t expect it to bring me anything close to joy, but seeing such a talented artist bring my poetry to life is a close approximation.
.
.
.
something i don’t think i have mentioned about valkyrie is that it may be my last book of poetry for the foreseeable future. i do have another collection in progress, but my career as a ya author has taken a massive positive turn in a way i could never have predicted. things appear to be moving slowly from the outside, but from my perspective i am working on my novels almost constantly. all i ever wanted to do was tell stories, and poetry has been an unexpected way to do that. i am so grateful for it, and i am so grateful for your love and support. i hope you’ll understand. by the way, of all the collections i have worked on, valkyrie is far and away the one i am most proud of. so i guess i’ll go out with a bang. 🖤
.
.
.

text:
due process protections and the #metoo era
#
signs at a “#metoo” demonstration during the second annual women’s march in cambridge, mass., january 20, 2018. (brian snyder/reuters) i was traveling friday and missed a rather interesting and consequential story. lisa borders, the ceo of time’s up, an “organization born of the #metoo movement that advocates for safe and harassment-free workplaces,” has resigned. why? because her son was accused of sexual assault. but that’s not what makes the story truly notable. family troubles can cause people to press pause on their careers all the time. what’s notable is that the ceo resigned in part to advocate for her son’s innocence: borders made it clear to time’s up leadership that she planned to proactively defend her son, someone close to the situation who was not authorized to discuss it publicly, and so spoke on the condition of anonymity, told the washington post. this created a difficult tension within the organization, whose mission revolves around believing survivors of sexual abuse. in response, time’s up put out a statement that said, in part, that it “unequivocally supports all survivors of sexual harassment and abuse” and that “all of our actions were fully guided by our support for survivors.” here’s the statement in…
link: https://metoozoo.com/news/due-process-protections-and-the-metoo-era/

text:
alô, alô, a todas e todos de belém, pa. atenção para a oficina "uma vida sem violência: um direito de todas as mulheres!" a violência contra as mulheres se constitui como uma grave violação aos direitos humanos e um sério problema de saúde pública. segundo a onu, o brasil é o 5º país que mais mata mulheres no mundo.

a violência de gênero têm sido um grande obstáculo para a manutenção da vida das mulheres, especialmente, no caso das mulheres negras: - as mulheres negras representam 68,8% das mulheres mortas por agressão (ministério da justiça/2015)
- índice de mulheres que entram em contato com o disque 180:  negras: 60,53% | brancas: 38,22% | amarelas 0,76% | indígenas 0,49% (spm, 2016)
- as mulheres negras representam 77% das mulheres que sofrem agressões físicas durante alguma gestação ao longo da vida (pcsvdfmulher/2016)
- as mulheres negras na faixa etária entre 16 e 24 anos, tem três vezes mais probabilidade de serem estupradas do que as mulheres brancas (spm-pr, 2003)
- entre 2003 e 2013, houve uma queda de 9,8% no total de feminicídios de mulheres brancas e o crescimento de 54,2% nos casos de feminicídio de mulheres negras (flacso, 2015)

por essa razão que o ceert, com o apoio do @institutoavon, tomou a iniciativa de realizar oficinas ao redor do país, com ações em porto alegre, salvador, belo horizonte e agora em belém. também ocorrerá um seminário em são paulo (informações em breve). venha discutir conosco. enfrentar esses desafios, conjuntamente, é um desafio todas e todos!

text:
so the other day i was doing some light reading online by some left winged news outlets on rape and the predominant articles were focused on how rape effects women and i barely saw anything on men. now it’s very well known but often ignored but there is an underrepresentation on male rape and i have firsthand witnessed many people claiming it’s not as severe and it’s not as damaging. now your views on it may differ greatly from mine, you might think male rape is worse than female rape or vice versa, that is just your opinion and you are allowed to have that, but the facts are still that male rape is underrepresented and downplayed severely. i decided to compile a very short list comparing the different problems two sexes face (not including any other sexes or genders because i wanted to keep this list short). if you want any source for the information (since there is quite a lot of different outlets i used) please either dm me asking about it or just comment requesting it because i have been rather vague with my points in order to summarise them into a short post. what are your thoughts and opinions on this topic? i’m curious to know what our demographic (of like, 5 followers) believe. have a nice day!
-a

~

text:
“i used to think that the world is fair. that it was a meritocracy. i no longer believe that. i think people who think it is an even playing field are probably like me - they have had it easy their whole life.”⁣
⁣
that’s mike gamson, svp of global solutions at @linkedin, who founded the company’s women's initiative to support women with advancing their careers.⁣
⁣
through this effort, mike has increased the percentage of women in senior leadership roles from 6% several years ago to 30% today, within the global solutions division.⁣
⁣
read the full interview on @forbes using the link in my bio. ⬆️⁣
.⁣
.⁣
.⁣
.⁣

text:
i dag har jeg skrevet et leserinnlegg i @btno som er veldig personlig og nært. jeg pleier aldri å skrive den type innlegg ettersom det er et sårbart tema for meg....
men etter å ha fulgt debatten de siste ukene om ulike menn i offentligheten som ikke tar ansvar for seksuell trakassering de har bedrevet over tid - og tror at det å si unnskyld er et virkemiddel for at slik atferd blir automatisk tilgitt og glemt er oppsiktsvekkende og provoserende. deres uttalelser vitner om lavt refleksjonsnivå rundt konsekvensene av deres forkastelige oppførsel. 
mitt innlegg er ikke ment som en historie om meg, men heller ett eksempel av mange, på hvordan uønsket seksuell trakassering og hvordan seksuelle overgrep kan påvirke ofrene psykisk. jeg håper med dette innlegget at man kan være mer åpne rundt konsekvensene ofre sitter igjen med psykisk - og at enkelte mennesker våger å kjenne på skyld og ansvar, istedenfor å gjemme seg bak skam, unnskyldninger og bortforklaringer.

amen👊🤘✍️💪!!

text: i don’t often make full posts about my story and history of eating disorders on this account anymore, especially now that i have @creativeed 🥳💗 but in celebration of national eating disorder awareness week, i wanted to share this post by creative education about a poem i had written when i was in residential eating disorder treatment the first time around📝the thing is, at the time, i didn’t intend for these words to ever be a poem, or to ever be seen by anyone. they were simply my thoughts pouring onto the page faster than i could keep up with. eating disorders are real, they are prevalent, and they are absolute hell.  i have lived 9 years under the rules and consequences of my mental illness, and i will continue to use my voice to help others who may not be able to speak🙏🏼 #endthestigma @neda

text: our bodies, including our brains, naturally react to events in certain ways. neurofeedback has the ability to increase stability and resiliency in the face of traumatic stress in ways that have not been permanently possible with drugs or talk therapy alone. many of these reactions have not been within our cognitive awareness or control. neurofeedback empowers the brain to more quickly and easily make changes in neuropathways that lead to flourishing, and this is why i cannot help but study in this field. i am excited to share that my professional journey into biofeedback and neurofeedback has officially begun and i am looking forward to seeing how it helps clients in my coaching practice. #lovepoweredlife #neurofeedback #heartmath #1john418

text: " when it comes down to it, knowing that it is our bodies that react first, with our thoughts, behavior and actions following, that helps us to determine when a moment has gone from peaceful to stress reactive. it’s like a dance where our own self-awareness helps to influence the flow of choreography for others. the term self-regulation is an accurate description of the action and outcome of using our embodied resources and timbo tools from one moment to the next. with this ability we can participate in the co-regulation of those around us. “co-regulation is a term that began as a description of adult support for infants, but is now used to describe an interactive process of regulatory support that can occur within the context of caring relationships across the lifespan” (rosanbalm, et al., 2017). co-regulation can happen naturally when we use all of our skills to self-regulate." #vulnerability #connection #relationshipgoals #yoga #traumarecovery #community #wellbeing #wellness #mindfulness #women #womenempowerment #woman #men #metoo

text:
ĺa sororite en actes : samedi 16 mars, rencontre au sommet entre chloé delaume et clara dupuy morency !

aux mêmes éditions québécoises triptyque qui ont édité les désormais fameux « argonautes » de maggie nelson, a paru récemment « mère d’invention » : premier livre, essai brillant et protéiforme, de clara dupuis-morency. elle nous fait la joie de venir au monte-en-l’air lors de sa venue exceptionnelle en france. l’auteure, spécialiste de proust, y traite de son avortement puis de la naissance de ses jumelles, et d’une thèse défendue entre deux, y questionne la sororité, l’empowerment, le rapport féminin à la douleur, la médecine, la création, la maternité évidemment, de façon très personnelle et parfois inattendue. c’est drôle, effronté, enlevé, provoquant, tellurique, angoissé, viscéral, émouvant, intelligent, cérébral… en un mot… fé.mi.nin ! 
de ce non renoncement aux parties qui nous composent, ainsi mobilisées toutes entières dans l’écriture, on repense au texte de jana cerna qui nous avait tant plu : « pas dans le cul aujourd’hui », et à une certaine chloé delaume, du « cri du sablier » aux « sorcières de la république », qui a révolutionné la façon de concevoir lecture et écriture pour clara dupuy-morency.
et bien justement, chloé delaume nous fera l’honneur de sa présence. elle discutera avec clara dupuy morency, et présentera son nouveau livre, mes bien chères sœurs (le seuil) paru en mars 2019.  également hybride, il est à la fois un long billet d’humeur, un manifeste subjectif d’une troublante sincérité, investi d’expériences intimes et d’humour, sur la sororité, et un éloge des mouvements historiques qui ont produit ce qu’elle célèbre comme la « quatrième vague » du féminisme, au travers de l’hashtag #metoo. « mes bien chères sœurs » invite à danser sur l’eau et à invoquer de nos vœux l’apocalypse ! (si si !) #lemontenlair #montenlair #lemonteenlair #monteenlair #librairielemontenlair #chloedelaume #claradupuismorency #meredinvention #mesbiencheressoeurs #sororite #feminisme #librairie #librairieparis #paris #paris20 #75020 #estparisien #parisian #bouquins #menilmontant #livres #terrasse #bookshop #book #bookstagram#metoo

aux mêmes éditions québécoises triptyque qui ont édité les désormais fameux « argonautes » de maggie nelson, a paru récemment « mère d’invention » : premier livre, essai brillant et protéiforme, de clara dupuis-morency. elle nous fait la joie de venir au monte-en-l’air lors de sa venue exceptionnelle en france. l’auteure, spécialiste de proust, y traite de son avortement puis de la naissance de ses jumelles, et d’une thèse défendue entre deux, y questionne la sororité, l’empowerment, le rapport féminin à la douleur, la médecine, la création, la maternité évidemment, de façon très personnelle et parfois inattendue. c’est drôle, effronté, enlevé, provoquant, tellurique, angoissé, viscéral, émouvant, intelligent, cérébral… en un mot… fé.mi.nin ! 
de ce non renoncement aux parties qui nous composent, ainsi mobilisées toutes entières dans l’écriture, on repense au texte de jana cerna qui nous avait tant plu : « pas dans le cul aujourd’hui », et à une certaine chloé delaume, du « cri du sablier » aux « sorcières de la république », qui a révolutionné la façon de concevoir lecture et écriture pour clara dupuy-morency.
et bien justement, chloé delaume nous fera l’honneur de sa présence. elle discutera avec clara dupuy morency, et présentera son nouveau livre, mes bien chères sœurs (le seuil) paru en mars 2019.  également hybride, il est à la fois un long billet d’humeur, un manifeste subjectif d’une troublante sincérité, investi d’expériences intimes et d’humour, sur la sororité, et un éloge des mouvements historiques qui ont produit ce qu’elle célèbre comme la « quatrième vague » du féminisme, au travers de l’hashtag #metoo. « mes bien chères sœurs » invite à danser sur l’eau et à invoquer de nos vœux l’apocalypse ! (si si !) #lemontenlair #montenlair #lemonteenlair #monteenlair #librairielemontenlair #chloedelaume #claradupuismorency #meredinvention #mesbiencheressoeurs #sororite #feminisme #librairie #librairieparis #paris #paris20 #75020 #estparisien #parisian #bouquins #menilmontant #livres #terrasse #bookshop #book #bookstagram#metoo

text:
não é uma indireta para ninguém! 
quero de fato te lembrar, me lembrar, lembrar a todos que tudo que é postado na internet não descreve nem ilustra integralmente ninguém! 
aquelas fotos de um artista, de um influenciador digital, de um amigo, de um conhecido, de um desconhecido, não traduzem os pensamentos, anseios, angústias, sentimentos, planos.

por mais detalhadas que sejam as postagens, a vida na internet é editável! postamos o que queremos, da forma que queremos.

não me refiro necessariamente à redes sociais. falo dos perfis em qualquer banco de dados.

se pensarmos em um site de busca de empregos, por exemplo. as informações que colocamos ali descrevem nossa carreira profissional somente.

nossas habilidades para resolver problemas, nossa habilidade (ou não) para dialogar com público, etc não estão ali. para ser efetivado em uma vaga, precisamos passar por entrevistas pessoalmente com recrutadores, líderes de setor, etc.

ou seja, precisam nos conhecer pessoalmente.

seguindo no raciocínio, se olharmos o perfil de alguém (e até o nosso) na internet, veremos a tal pessoa feliz, com suas comidas e pessoas preferidas, passeando por lugares que pra ela são importantes, dizendo frases elaboradas, etc. 
mas e a vida que acontece por trás da lente do celular? a vida real, sabe? o que tem passado no feed? 
se no seu ‘feed da vida real’ tem passado algo além do que está no seu feed da rede social, o mesmo pode acontecer com a pessoa que você está seguindo!

pense nisso!

se precisar de apoio para lidar com algo que está difícil de entender na sua vida privada, fique à vontade para entrar em contato comigo!

text:
in talk at notre dame, #metoo founder says the movement's goal is 'the work of healing'
by south bend tribune reporter greg swiercz
south bend — tarana burke launched the metoo movement in 2006 but it changed dramatically in 2017, when the hashtag #metoo unleashed a worldwide social media phenomenon that focused on sexual assault.
burke explained the evolution of the movement — from her journey of discovery as a teen to the impact that #metoo has had in confronting sexual violence — at the university of notre dame on monday night, in a conversation with notre dame professor maria mckenna in the debartolo classroom building.
burke is senior director at girls for gender equity in brooklyn. there, as in her early life, she helps girls coping with the effects of sexual violence.
read the full story at southbendtribune.com.
photo: tarana burke, founder of the metoo movement, speaks monday night at the university of notre dame about her work in helping sexual assault victims. tribune photo by greg swiercz
#metoo #notredame #tanaraburke #sexualviolence #healing #girlsforgenderequity

text:
siempre que después de un “yo no soy machista” vaya un pero... huid, es machista.
•
lo mismo pasa con quienes “no son racistas, pero” o “no son homófobos, pero”.
•
no hay nada que pueda añadirse detrás de una afirmación como “no soy machista” y que empiece con un pero.
•
de entrada, lo más acertado sería decir “soy feminista o estoy a favor del feminismo”. si directamente evita esa palabra... es porque no está de acuerdo con sus principios.

text:
as a little girl i was told to walk quietly so i walked on my toes, to speak when spoken to so i held my tongue. don’t draw attention to yourself with outfits, don’t eat too much because fat is unattractive,  don’t talk back in case it makes people angry, don’t cry in public, be humble, don’t make a scene, avoid conflict and lastly to be myself. ha! 
basically i was trained to be invisible. i have always been a good fly on the wall. on stage and in my writing is where i now have a voice, a face and an outfit that stands out. 
i am not blaming, we are all doing our best but i am aware of how this impacted me and i recognize similar behaviours in some of my vocal students today. 
social obedience and control led me to depression, repression, alcohol abuse, years of therapy and into and out of abusive relationships where i tolerated too much bad behaviour because i didn’t know myself enough to stand up for myself or have a voice. 
change comes through educating young girls of their human rights to respect, freedom of speech, choice and safety. these concepts have to be taught and encouraged if we want transformation.
 let’s let our daughters, youth and students know they are worthy and  loved no matter what. don’t always expect more from them. if they are loved and heard and seen they will gain the confidence to become all they can be. 
we are all unique, here on purpose and for a reason and can’t spread our wings unless we are grounded and know we are special already.  we are good enough as we are. we don’t have to prove it or conform to be loved. then we can make our make a sound, own ourselves, speak our truth, be a vision even if it may create discomfort and conflict for those around us. .

#change #voice #freedom #emancipation #love #beyourself #empowerment #songwriter #lilyfrost @suzkasound @bobackmakesmusic @tiabrazdamusic @deniellebassels @thelaurageiger @kristynfoulger @jocelyn_claire_burke @rebeccaeverettmusic @kinniestarr @katyofthebay @sideshowami @catherinealexandriaelizabeth #metoo #humanrights #feminism #womenpower #womensvoices #emanciapation #change #beyourself #knowyourself #speakyourtruth #makeasound #makeamark #socialpressure @jodenerussell

as a little girl i was told to walk quietly so i walked on my toes, to speak when spoken to so i held my tongue. don’t draw attention to yourself with outfits, don’t eat too much because fat is unattractive,  don’t talk back in case it makes people angry, don’t cry in public, be humble, don’t make a scene, avoid conflict and lastly to be myself. ha! 
basically i was trained to be invisible. i have always been a good fly on the wall. on stage and in my writing is where i now have a voice, a face and an outfit that stands out. 
i am not blaming, we are all doing our best but i am aware of how this impacted me and i recognize similar behaviours in some of my vocal students today. 
social obedience and control led me to depression, repression, alcohol abuse, years of therapy and into and out of abusive relationships where i tolerated too much bad behaviour because i didn’t know myself enough to stand up for myself or have a voice. 
change comes through educating young girls of their human rights to respect, freedom of speech, choice and safety. these concepts have to be taught and encouraged if we want transformation.
 let’s let our daughters, youth and students know they are wohy and  loved no matter what. don’t always expect more from them. if they are loved and heard and seen they will gain the confidence to become all they can be. 
we are all unique, here on purpose and for a reason and can’t spread our wings unless we are grounded and know we are special already.  we are good enough as we are. we don’t have to prove it or conform to be loved. then we can make our make a sound, own ourselves, speak our truth, be a vision even if it may create discomfo and conflict for those around us. .

text:
🔥breaking gin news🔥: hendricks to launch a new expression - midsummer solstice.

the gin is the first expression to launch from master distiller lesley gracie’s “cabinet of curiosities”, which is said to be “a place of experimental botanic alchemy” at the hendricks gin palace in scotland.

hendrick’s midsummer solstice has been inspired by the “mysterious and ephemeral delights” of floral blooms during the summer solstice.

the new bottling is said to be true to the hendrick’s original house style, but is infused with floral essences and flavours that capture the “aromatic intensity of a midsummer day”.
.
gracie said: “i have always been enamoured by the power of nature’s flavours and aromas at the peak of summer and for this new expression i’ve hand-selected each floral essence to capture this intensity.
.
“midsummer solstice joins a long line of innovations from hendrick’s and i’m excited to not only create new expressions at the gin palace, but also share them with curious tasters and gin explorers all over the world.”
.
hendrick’s midsummer solstice will launch in the uk next month and then in the us in may. bottled at 43.4% abv, the launch will be supported with “significant” marketing investment.

source: https://www.thespiritsbusiness.com/2019/02/hendricks-launches-first-gin-from-cabinet-of-curiosities/

.

text:
grateful to have caroline macgillivray part of our panel for this year's women's awareness week  #iwd2019 in vancouver. .
.
caroline macgillivray designs workshops and programs to promote health and wellness in the corporate and not for profit sector. caroline is a popular speaker, writer, medical qi gong therapist, yoga teacher and workshop leader.  she believes we need to unplug, breathe and be. she is has been involved with  initiatives such as qi day and bunny yoga fundraising classes for small animal rescue. she has also taught workshops for kids and parents for safe online outreach society.  caroline is best known for founding beauty night society, an award-winning charity that provides programs to build self esteem and change the lives of vulnerable people through wellness, life skills development and make overs. in 18 years, beauty night society has given 70, 000 life-makeovers to women who live in poverty.
.
. 
the well beings & weekend rituals (march 4, 9 & 10) https://iwd2019vancouver.eventbrite.ca or the link in @minibarcanada’s profile.

text:
as far as i have come with my ppd i still have really hard days.  they are few and far between but they can hit like a ton of bricks.  the hardest thing to do on those days is to allow myself to withdraw from family activities and to take alone time.  it’s not that i don’t want it, but there is a guilt i associate with it.  will i miss out on the kids doing something for the first time? will my husband be resentful if he has them by himself all day? am i being dramatic? is this selfish? 
the answer is no.  and while it’s easier said then done it is necessary.  we must take care of ourselves.  we must listen to our bodies and our minds.  it doesn’t have to be all day but it should be for a bit every day. take a walk, take a run, listen to some music, take a long shower, do something for you. 😘

#shareyourstory #freeyourmind #youdownwithppd #momminainteasy #momlife #wereinthistogether #momsupport #beyourownadvocate #speakup #everythingwillbeokay #thistooshallpass #yourestrongerthanyothink #youwillgetthruthis

text:
​​#историичитателей #нуженсовет

я понимаю что моя история не такая печальная как у многих авторов этой группы, но все же я не знаю как поступить, поэтому прошу совета.

мне 26 лет, родом из узбекистана, сейчас живу в южной корее. приехала, как и многие, на заработки.

отца никогда не было. мама ненавидит мужчин. уже больше года живу с молодым человеком, копим на свадьбу и на будущее.

сегодня мой любимый и любящий человек причинил мне очень большую боль. мы сидели в интернете, смотрели всякие видеоролики, тут попалось одно видео, где двое молодых людей грязно обсуждали девушек, что и как они бы с ними сделали,(как оказалось, это был какой-то дурацкий пранк). я разозлилась, стала ругаться на них, и тут почувствовала удар по бедру. а потом мой молодой человек стал орать, что я рассуждаю как старая бабка. он ударил меня смартфоном и вышел курить. я слышала как он плачет, потом весь вечер просил прощения, сказал, что больше не будет и т.д... я не знаю что мне делать? остаться или уйти? он действительно раскаялся, когда плакал или это временно? ведь между нами ещё много будет несоответствий... и как мне можно изменить поведение чтобы такое больше не повторялось? или это невозможно изменить? столько вопросов и я не нахожу ответов.
=================
из писем в @nemolchi.uz. вы можете отправить свою историю анонимно: https://goo.gl/forms/3nvmqxaflb5dq5b92

внимание: под личными историями запрещены оскорбительные, обесценивающие и унижающие автора комментарии. если вы случайно оставили такой комментарий, пожалуйста, удалите его. в противном случае мы удалим его вместе с вами, не вступая в новые дискуссии.

text:
ieri sera abbiamo partecipato all'assemblea pubblica di nonunadimeno modena.
si è parlato dell'8 marzo e di come organizzare a modena lo sciopero globale femminista indetto dalla rete @nonunadimeno.
come opop accoglienza sosteniamo questa iniziativa: uno dei punti cardine emerso dal collettivo di modena è la consapevolezza che la legge 132 (immigrazione e sicurezza) andrà a impattare in maniera decisiva sulle donne migranti, andandole a privare di quei pochi diritti di cui godevano in precedenza. l'abrogazione della protezione umanitaria cancella la speranza, per quelle donne che hanno subìto violenze di ogni genere durante il viaggio, di costruirsi un nuovo futuro, negandogli un permesso di soggiorno che gli consentirebbe di iniziare una nuova vita e inserirsi nel tessuto sociale.

invitiamo tutte e tutti a partecipare allo sciopero dell'8 marzo, portando avanti la propria battaglia ma sempre uniti per il rispetto dei diritti e della dignità umana.

text:
guess what y'all? we are a few days away from #womenshistory month and we are so excited to get started with posts about women. for too long, women and our ideas were kept in the background. can you believe that in 2019 there are still spaces that silence women? i have attended several churches where there are no women in leadership, yet the majority of the congregation is made up of women. how do we continue to allow this? women have amazing, important, and relevant ideas and perspectives that are beneficial to all. stand up and be heard! push past the fear of anonymity and be counted for your great ideas.  i want to congratulate all of you beautiful and wonderfully made women.  you are seen and appreciated! give yourself a big loving hug! you're so important!⠀
.⠀
.⠀
.⠀

text: saying no - photographers may often try to persuade models into shooting topless when they don’t feel comfortable doing so by telling them to ‘cover their nipples’ or that they’ll only shoot from one point upwards. this is often impossible to maintain throughout a shoot and leads to models ending up doing something they don’t want to do - and the images will exist forever. you cannot trust a stranger to do what they say they will, no matter how nice they seem. if someone tries to manipulate you in this way, all that is needed is to say that you don’t feel comfortable - you don’t need a reason to say no. 🙌🏽

text:
(1/2) you sit across me, deep in thought, you stroke your lips as you stare into nothingness. there's a heaviness in your presence, like you carry the weight of the entire world on your chest. there is a sadness about your eyes, like they could cry a million tears and never dry. those creases at the corners are the intricacies of an artist. that makes me believe in god. your eyes bring out the mother in me, i want to cradle you in my arms and put your sorrows to sleep. poetry flows from the folds of your forehead as you frown. you hum an almost recognisable tune, the song of loss. the reddish corners of your eye, burn with passion yet speak of longing in cold nights. your artistic fingertips is where i want to find myself. you catch me looking at you and there's sultry in my glances, you raise your eyebrow questioning me, my heart beats a little bit faster, a rhythm so divine. i look out the door as usual, and wonder why i always have my eyes on the exit. you walk towards my chair, there is a sense of belonging to the way i inhale the smell of your cologne mixed with your own scent, but it's followed by an exhale of what screams of abandonment, like someone inside me wailing for someone that never left. my body tells me this won't last. i ignore every ounce of it. we engage in a conversation. somewhere your words never find me, and mine never find yours. a mundane conversation. i nod. you nod. i look into your eyes, your's fixated on mine. you slide you fingers through my hair playfully, it mutes the entire room crowded with noisy strangers. some mundane conversation? again. somewhere you put in a sentence so heavy that my heart can't take it. what have you been through? i wonder. what about you feels so close yet distant? what is it? i can't put my finger on it. i move across the tables and reach for the exit. it's time to leave. like you will, someday? maybe. you reach for a hug, curl your arms around me. i reciprocate. marlboro, hmm. your breath is warm. it touches my face the way sunlight touches the balcony on a summer morning. your sweater has a feel to it, it reminds me of mornings at the bread maker with my grandfather.
. 
this picture is of @ayush007

text:
though tanushree has decided to not label herself a christian she does professional to have had an encounter with jesus and is influenced by his teachings. but her recent trip to india (she's been living in the states for the past few years) where she inadvertently kick-started the metoo movement made me realize she is a lot like another biblical character - queen esther.
queen esther was a common jewish woman living in a foreign land with her uncle. the king of that land became unhappy with his wife, banished her and held a sort of contest to choose his new queen. and esther won the contest and became the queen. later, a few conspirators hatched a plan to kill all the jews. esther's uncle heard of the plan and planned with esther to approach the king and tell him if this plan and use her influence to change his mind. she does that and saves her people.
tanushree never imagined she would be used by god to kick start such a moment. and even though she might not have saved many people, she has through her bravery paved the way for other women to speak out and have a better chance to be heard than in previous years. and come on, both esther and tanushree were beauty queens!!

did they ever?
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

be safe, be secure - act smart 
these bumper stickers looks trendy! 
not only do these stickers give strangers too much personal information about your family specifically, a good criminal can discern a lot more information that could put you at harm.

from this  information it can be determined what hours you will be home, whether you have a pet such as a dog, and even whether or not your house has guns in it..
stay safe and keep your information private. you don’t need to take unnecessary risk & troubles... #wethefemale #strongwomensafecommunities #empoweringwomen #selfdefense #personalsecurity #metoo #homesecurity #feminism #besafe

text: you know some of us are weathering storms you couldn’t possibly fathom?  i wanted this ig to look pretty for you all. so i would post and delete but i want my ig to be completely authentic. without fully indulging. i encourage you all to check on your friends and family. now!!! stop reading this and ask them are they really ok. do it now!!!a lot of us are suffering in silence. all these polished images on instagram are a beautiful distraction of the darkness that’s going on in this world. however don’t forget to be empathetic to those literally living through it. some of the sickest, cruelest things happen to people you couldn’t imagine. please hug your loved ones tight, send that text and apology now. you can’t imagine what some of us are going through man. you know that scream cry to god, that feeling that your pain is legit about to kill you. yea i feel that right now. your pain is real if no one else does i see you.i will free my self from all this trauma because this little guy deserves a happy & healthy mommy so i can help him even more. i just want you to know if your hurting your not alone and you absolutely can call on me for some support #metoo #survivor #trauma #insomnia #iknowithurts #imhurt but it will get better🤞🏿🤞🏿#metoomovement

posted @withrepost • @yeancha_o candid!
if you know you know!

violence against women and girls is rooted in gender-based discrimination and social norms and gender stereotypes that perpetuate such violence. given the devastating effect violence has on women, efforts have mainly focused on responses and services for survivors. however, the best way to end violence against women and girls is to prevent it from happening in the first place by addressing its root and structural causes.

prevention should start early in life, by educating and working with young boys and girls promoting respectful relationships and gender equality. working with youth is a “best bet” for faster, sustained progress on preventing and eradicating gender-based violence. while public policies and interventions often overlook this stage of life, it is a critical time when values and norms around gender equality are forged.

together we can achieve more........ oseni ibrahim

text:
♡脅迫②♡
・
・
2019年2月26日 18:25 
今日の晩御飯中に娘がつけたのは
2018年11月3日の嵐にしやがれ
遠藤憲一記念館の場面で
「全部妄想です」
と何回もワードが出る
多加子が私に送ってきた書面と同じ
相変わらずな態度
娘にさせる人間も最低だが
それを受ける娘も最低。
今日も晩御飯がまずい。
楽しくない。
唯一子供と見る1日1時間の番組がこれ
しんどい。
ホンマに離婚間近の
生理的に無理な相手になりそうだ

妄想と思いたければ勝手に思えばいい。
私は自分が感じたことを日記に書き続けるだけ。
誰に言いたいわけでもない。
コメントもいらない。
もし私が道端で刺されたら何も残らないので日記に書くだけ。
実際、セクハラを訴えてから何回車に引かれそうになったか…
それは私しか知らないだろう。
知らない人間がとやかく口出しするな。
どんな#脅迫 をしても犯罪に上乗せされるだけ
やった事は消えない
消せない
そんな事をするのは自分が負けそうだからじゃないかな？
全部妄想ですと最後まで言い切れる
世間を説得出来るなら
そんなあがく必要なんてない
違うかな 【追加】
私はこの投稿を食事中にしてた訳だが、
気づいたのか娘は急いでご飯を済ませ
洗面所に行った
その後大人しくなり別室の和室にこもった
いつも何かと洗面所にこもる
洗面所に何かあるんだろうか…
・
・
