text:
i den forrige posten sa vi at mange av de som utøver seksuell trakassering har mangelfull kunnskap om hva seksuell trakassering egentlig er. så hva blir definert som seksuell trakassering?⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i likestillings. og diskrimineringsloven §13 blir seksuell trakassering definert som: med seksuell trakassering menes enhver form for uønsket seksuell oppmerksomhet som har som formål eller virkning å være krenkende, skremmende, fiendtlig, nedverdigende, ydmykende eller plagsom.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
det vil si at dersom en person gjør noe for å krenke en annen seksuelt, f.eks. å si noe seksuelt ydmykende, så er det å regne som seksuell trakassering. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
men det er også seksuell trakassering dersom en person gjør noe for å flørte eller "bare på kødd" men virkningen for den som utsettes for det er f.eks. plagsom. for eksempel dersom en person tar en annen på rumpen uten å mene noe negativt med det, men den som blir tatt på opplever det som plagsomt eller krenkende. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i neste post skal vi gå enda mer konkret inn på hva seksuell trakassering kan innebære. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

stop_filter_tweet: den forrige posten sa vi mange av de som utøver seksuell trakassering har mangelfull kunnskap om hva seksuell trakassering egentlig er . så hva blir define som seksuell trakassering ? ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ likestillings . og diskrimineringsloven §13 blir seksuell trakassering define som : med seksuell trakassering menes enhver form uønsket seksuell oppmerksomhet som har som formål eller virkning å være krenkende , skremmende , fiendtlig , nedverdigende , ydmykende eller plagsom.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ det vil si dersom en person gjør noe å krenke en annen seksuelt , f.eks . å si noe seksuelt ydmykende , så er det å regne som seksuell trakassering . ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ men det er også seksuell trakassering dersom en person gjør noe å fløe eller `` bare på kødd '' men virkningen den som utsettes det er f.eks . plagsom . eksempel dersom en person tar en annen på rumpen uten å mene noe negativt med det , men den som blir tatt på opplever det som plagsomt eller krenkende . ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ neste post skal vi gå enda mer konkret inn på hva seksuell trakassering kan innebære . ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ vil du lære mer om forebygging av seksuell trakassering ? se lenke bio . ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ eksuelltrakassering⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ etoo⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ rakassering⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ vergrep⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ orebygging⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ obbing⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ oldtekt⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ orebygge⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ oredrag⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ aerja⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ eiernei⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ tiftelsentryggere⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text: non, je ne suis pas charmante. d'ailleurs, j'en ai rien a faire de ton commentaire sur mon physique. tu peux le garder pour une fille qui te montrera vraiment de l'intérêt. moi, je n'ai rien demandé ! quand les mecs nous aborde avec cette phrase, ils pensent être sympa. on devrait être flattés : "trop bien un homme me trouve à son goût". mais en fait on s'en fiche, on ne vit pas pour que les hommes nous trouve à leur goût. on ne devrait pas vivre dans l'attente de la validation de notre personne par les hommes. mais on l'a trop intégré. 🔹je me souviens avoir grandie en considérant le harcelement de rue comme "normal". pas normal dans le sens où je devrais être flattée que les hommes me remarquent mais plutôt dans le sens "bah ouais, si je sors je vais être emmerdée". et je sais qu'on est beaucoup à etre comme ça.🔹 quand les mouvements #metoo et #balancetonporc ont éclaté, les hommes sont venus pleurer. "ouin ouin, on ne peut même plus draguer maintenant !". 🔸comme j'ai été en colère ! le pire je crois c'est que c'était très difficile d'en parler parce qu'en face, les hommes ne comprennent pas. alors, je m'énerve face à leur incompréhension. et on fini par le classique "tu t'enerve, je n'ai plus envie de t'écouter" qui m'achève et me rend complètement hystérique.🔹 attention, ne me faites pas dire ce que je n'ai pas dit : dans certaines circonstances, on peut en effet accepter le compliment. mais faut leur faire comprendre qu'on ne leur doit rien, qu'on n'a pas à les remercier de nous valider. qu'on n'a pas à se sentir flattée. les hommes doivent apprendre à écouter les femmes, écouter les signes et pas partir du principe que nous sommes un dû.
name: Je deviens Féministe

text:
le parquet de paris a classé sans suite lundi la plainte d'une comédienne qui accuse de viols l'influent producteur et réalisateur luc besson. il avait été une des personnalités mises en cause en france à la suite de la vague #metoo.

le parquet de paris a précisé à l'afp que les investigations n'ont "pas permis de caractériser l'infraction dénoncée dans tous ses éléments constitutifs". il ne conclut donc pas à une absence d'infraction mais estime qu'il n'y a pas assez d'éléments pour poursuivre la procédure.

la plaignante veut se constituer partie civile
l'avocat de la comédienne et mannequin belgo-néerlandaise âgée de 30 ans a annoncé à l'afp son intention de déposer une plainte avec constitution de partie civile afin d'obtenir la reprise des investigations par un juge d'instruction. "il y a des éléments à charge indiscutables, notamment des certificats médicaux", a souligné francis szpiner, son avocat, pour qui "le parquet s'est substitué aux juges d'instruction".
le 18 mai 2018, sand van roy avait porté plainte contre le producteur de la série des "taxi", au lendemain d'un rendez-vous dans un palace parisien, le bristol.

neuf autres femmes avaient par la suite accusé le réalisateur du "grand bleu" de gestes déplacés, voire d'agressions sexuelles, lors de témoignages recueillis par mediapart pour des faits en grande partie prescrits. certaines ont écrit aux enquêteurs ou ont été auditionnées en appui de la plaignante.
entendu en audition libre le 2 octobre par les policiers, luc besson avait ensuite été confronté en décembre à son accusatrice, chacun restant sur ses positions.

le parquet a par ailleurs indiqué, vendredi, avoir ouvert une autre enquête après un signalement de faits d'agression sexuelle concernant le cinéaste. la police judiciaire de paris a été saisie pour vérifications après les propos d'une femme révélés par mediapart accusant #lucbesson de gestes déplacés en 2002.

après l'islamologue tariq ramadan, le ministre gérald darmanin ou le comédien #philippecaubère, luc besson avait été à son tour une des figures françaises prises dans la vague d'accusations de femmes affirmant avoir été victimes de viols ou d'agressions sexuelles.

results from a survey for the charity brook released today have reconfirmed that sexual misconduct is rife at uk universities, with more than half of students saying they’ve experienced something, and only a fraction of those report the incident. .
we’re doing all we can with our report + support software, which almost 30 uk universities license, to make reporting accessible to everyone. our online reporting tool is a safe and secure space, where students can make a named report if they wish, or remain anonymous. vitally, they can also seek support online.

and this is what remains. 
you.
you and the divine.

fuck religion.
fuck the constructs.
fuck society that has kept us small.

step into the divine.
be that now!

it is done.
in one, in all, in love.
amen.
maria.

text:
in november 2017, at team of 30 advocates set out to touch lives of girls living on kalangala island. we went to different schools and communities plus landing sites to sensitise people about the benefits of educating girls and supporting them to realize their full potential. 
we also met girls at bery glaser 's place who we spent an evening with talking to them about their rights, the importance of keeping in school and the need to break the silence if they are sexually abused. 
none of the girls mentioned the torture they were going through and am sure it's because they were threatened and stopped from speaking out the truth.
we left with an impression that they were doing well, going to school,  having meals regularly and receiving medical care when they fell sick. 
all these were lies. 
they were all being sexually abused every night. those that refused were denied education sponsorship and meals sometimes while others were chased away.

i had the opportunity to speak one on one with some girls but non of them ever mentioned that they were being seriously harassed. some requested me to get them sponsors for their education ( now i understand that these could be the ones that had refused to give in the the demands of their master. 
these girls ran to this home to hide from the relatives that were sexually abusing them only to fall into a much bigger pit.
i feel so sad that they had to endure all this for years without help.
this home has been operating illegally and whereas some of the district officials in kalangala district were aware, they never closed up this home. the police in kalangala new about this but never helped the children. 
like it was reported in the daily monitor yesterday,  it's actually one of the police officials in kalangala that told bery to run away after knowing that there was a team coming from kampala to arrest him.
the question is who is meant to protect the children of uganda if not those in positions of leadership!!! corruption has become the order of the day at the expense of the innocent girls.
#nowhitesaviors #justiceforgirls #kalangalatoo #metoo #countmein
#endsextrafficking
#endviolence

text:
content note: pell, childhood sexual assault (no details). i haven't signed this yet but it feels right to share this painting i did today. this work is called "rise". it's a companion piece to the "climb" and "dive" paintings (which i need to individually photograph and put online) but is also separate. they're all about the continuous process of healing, of living with illness and trauma. 
they all have tension between the serene colours and the energetic brushmarks but "rise" is especially about childhood sexual assault. the person who assaulted me was a painter. for a long time after i kept making art, and then i mostly stopped. it hurt too much, triggered too much, and i was also punishing myself. last year i started painting again. this work is about the pain, yes, but also the reclamation. [image descriptions: photos of an abstract acrylic painting on a3 watercolour paper in perylene green, phthalo turquoise, raw sienna, and titanium white.]
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
a former senior trump campaign staffer monday filed a lawsuit in federal court against the president, accusing him of sexual assault during his 2016 campaign

alva johnson says trump grabbed her hand and kissed her without her consent ahead of a campaign rally in tampa. in an interview with the washington post, johnson said, “i immediately felt violated because i wasn’t expecting it or wanting it. i can still see his lips coming straight for my face.” the lawsuit alleges that president trump forcibly kissed johnson in a campaign rv “in front of numerous other campaign officials.” johnson “felt reduced to just another object of defendant trump’s unwanted sexual attention,” according to the lawsuit, filed in the u.s. district court for the middle district of florida in tampa.

white house press secretary sarah sanders denied the allegations in a statement to the washington post. “this never happened and is directly contradicted by multiple highly credible eye witness accounts,” sanders wrote.

johnson also says she experienced racial discrimination while working for the president. “not only did ms. johnson endure forcible kissing by her boss, she experienced race and gender discrimination as one of the few females and one of only a handful of african american people on the campaign payroll,” the lawsuit states.

johnson initially consulted an attorney in 2016 after the access hollywood tape release because she recognized a similarity with what happened to her, according to the lawsuit.

johnson’a attorney, hassan a. zavareei, in a news release, said she eventually decided to come forth. “when she saw what her work on the campaign had wrought—a president who mocks the #metoo movement and undermines the dignity of the office with his sexist and racist behavior—she decided to seek justice.” johnson is seeking unspecified damages for emotional pain and suffering, the post reported.

four people confirmed to the new yorker that johnson told them about the incident afterward, but two others johnson says were present at the time of the assault said they did not see it.

#usa

text:
shame
the feeling that stays the longest post the abuse. along with sexual abuse comes the emotional manipulation, deception, shock and trauma of the entire episode. this leaves the mind processing information and subconsciously allowing self blame and guilt for not doing things differently.
h e a l i n g- there is no one way to recover from abuse. know that you did your best, it’s not your fault and you did not deserve it! love yourself in this space. show your mind and body some kindness.
#journeytolight

text:
we promised that we won't forget. 
we vowed that we'll fight. 
so here's the first step, first punch, first blow.

@suhayllo & i @ngitomakena will be screening two highly impactful award-winning films; 
kyenvu by kemiyondi coutinho @kemi_yondo
she matters by suhayl omar @suhayllo × she matters tribe @shematterstribe × gathigia kinyua @gathigiakinyua .  we'll also have an open discussion, engaging the audience with a few panelists, venting, raging, about the growing rape culture in kenya, and the normalcy around it.  the two films also focus on harassment & its normalization, and telling the stories of survivors.  come. come rage. 
on the 28th of february (thursday) from six pm, at @pawa254 's mageuzi theatre (3rd floor). entry is free, because the patriarchy has cost us enough already.  #wearescreaming
#enough
#metoo

text:
there are not many films that fell relevant and right 25 years after their release. but magalir mattum is one such gem.

a comedy that tackles the sensitive issue of sexual harassment at workplace, is all the more relevant now, in the wake of the #metoo movement in india, than it has ever been.

celebrating the silver jubilee, urvashi, the lead actor shared how magalir mattum was ahead of its time and spoke of workplace harassment and the male gaze. “to produce a project that tells the story from a woman’s point of view was an audacious attempt. and, he (kamal haasan) selected actresses who are not known for their glamorous roles,” said urvashi crediting kamal hasan and  singeetham for the movie's success.
.
.
.
#silverjubilee #magalirmattum #metooindian #workplaceharassment #inspiring #kamalhasan #tamilcinema

text:
le parquet de paris a classé sans suite lundi la plainte d'une comédienne qui accuse de viols l'influent producteur et réalisateur luc besson. il avait été une des personnalités mises en cause en france à la suite de la vague #metoo.

après neuf mois d'enquête, le parquet de paris a classé sans suite lundi 25 février la plainte d'une comédienne qui accuse de viols l'influent producteur et réalisateur luc besson. "monsieur luc besson a pris acte avec satisfaction de la décision du procureur de la république de classer sans suite les accusations portées par mme sand van roy, qu'il a toujours formellement démenties", a déclaré son avocat thierry marembert dans un communiqué adressé à l'afp.

le parquet de paris a précisé à l'afp que les investigations n'ont "pas permis de caractériser l'infraction dénoncée dans tous ses éléments constitutifs". il ne conclut donc pas à une absence d'infraction mais estime qu'il n'y a pas assez d'éléments pour poursuivre la procédure.

la plaignante veut se constituer partie civile

text:
вы заметили, что в мире несколько лет назад появилась новая, неведомая «нация» – «пользователи сети». их никто не видел, но они обладают необычным набором особенностей – они вечно чем-то недовольны, они постоянно что-то осуждают. и, самое главное, с их мнением почему-то считаются🙄
⠀
каждый день, пролистывая новостные сайты (профессия не отпускает, да), я натыкаюсь на материалы, которые рассказывают о «жизни» этой «нации». заголовки, кстати, говорят сами за себя – «пользователи сети раскритиковали платье очередной певицы», «фото актера категорически не понравилось пользователям сети» и так далее🤦‍♂️
⠀
впрочем, черт бы с ними, со звездами (хотя и их порой жалко) - популярность всегда идет за руку с хейтом, такой уж мир. но больше всего меня задевают ситуации, когда пресловутые «пользователи сети» влияют на принятие решений по действительно важным вопросам, при этом даже не пытаясь погрузиться в тему🤓
⠀
как бы страшно это не звучало, но происходит примерно так: сотни людей работают над проектом, проводят ночи в попытках найти оптимальные варианты, грезят о том, чтобы сделать мир лучше. а после в комменты под новостью о проекте приходит необразованный тролль, оставляет коммент в стиле «говно. нахер оно нужно?» и, вуаля, «пользователи сети не одобрили проект…»😐
⠀
исход у этого «не одобрили» может быть разным. бывает, что проект «замораживают» или отменяют вовсе. но, чаще всего, его автор проходит через годы или месяцы борьбы с теми самыми «пользователями», седеет, теряет последние нервные клетки, и все-таки реализует проект, чтобы увидеть как тот самый тролль делает на фоне его «детища» селфи🤳
⠀
как думаете, есть ли какой-то «рецепт» борьбы с этими «пользователями»? и когда, наконец, мы будем принимать решения без оглядки на их мнение? 🤒
⠀
p.s. снова подумываю о президентстве😂
⠀
#пользователисети #интернет #notoracism #metoo #hate #blackhistorymonth #руденокнашпрезидент #philosophy

stop_filter_tweet: вы заметили , что в мире несколько лет назад появилась новая , неведомая « нация » – « пользователи сети » . их никто не видел , но они обладают необычным набором особенностей – они вечно чем-то недовольны , они постоянно что-то осуждают . и , самое главное , с их мнением почему-то считаются🙄 ⠀ каждый день , пролистывая новостные сайты ( профессия не отпускает , да ) , я натыкаюсь на материалы , которые рассказывают о « жизни » этой « нации » . заголовки , кстати , говорят сами за себя – « пользователи сети раскритиковали платье очередной певицы » , « фото актера категорически не понравилось пользователям сети » и так далее🤦‍♂️ ⠀ впрочем , черт бы с ними , со звездами ( хотя и их порой жалко ) - популярность всегда идет за руку с хейтом , такой уж мир . но больше всего меня задевают ситуации , когда пресловутые « пользователи сети » влияют на принятие решений по действительно важным вопросам , при этом даже не пытаясь погрузиться в тему🤓 ⠀ как бы страшно это не звучало , но происходит примерно так : сотни людей работают над проектом , проводят ночи в попытках найти оптимальные варианты , грезят о том , чтобы сделать мир лучше . а после в комменты под новостью о проекте приходит необразованный тролль , оставляет коммент в стиле « говно . нахер оно нужно ? » и , вуаля , « пользователи сети не одобрили проект… » 😐 ⠀ исход у этого « не одобрили » может быть разным . бывает , что проект « замораживают » или отменяют вовсе . но , чаще всего , его автор проходит через годы или месяцы борьбы с теми самыми « пользователями » , седеет , теряет последние нервные клетки , и все-таки реализует проект , чтобы увидеть как тот самый тролль делает на фоне его « детища » селфи🤳 ⠀ как думаете , есть ли какой-то « рецепт » борьбы с этими « пользователями » ? и когда , наконец , мы будем принимать решения без оглядки на их мнение ? 🤒 ⠀ p.s . снова подумываю о президентстве😂 ⠀

text:
what did you do last night? did you get stuck between sweaty bods on a grubby tram? did you shake your fist at traffic? maybe you raised a sweat over dirty laundry, un-chopped vegetables or unwashed dishes? maybe you just did it all silently...muttering to yourself.
.
did you bend your partners ear about another day objectified, victimised, ignored or overlooked for opportunities at work?
.
what if next monday night you could skip all that rubbish and just skip to your local pub instead?
.
monday 4th march @ 6:30-9:30pm
grace darling hotel - collingwood
.
a night of union choir, spoken word and power pantsuits. celebrating international womens day.
.
if you have a story, a burden, a confession...cut it loose at the open mic. there is nothing more liberating than liberating yourself in three minutes in front of a room full of strangers.
.
details and rsvp: facebook event via my profile: “i am woman, hear me (w)raw”
.
https://www.facebook.com/events/2256347871274683/?ti=
.
https://www.unionwomen.org.au/spoken_word_wrawfest
.
@amy_bodossian @zaynabf_____ @koraly_poet @melbspokenword .
artwork: @i_fayd (check it out)
.
📸: kaliopi malamas, brendan bonsack, nathan james little
.

text:
⛧ angstanfald ⛧

for et par måneder siden havde jeg mit første og eneste angstanfald nogensinde. det blev udløst under en forelæsning på mit nye studie. jeg sad på anden række, længst væk fra døren. heldigvis ved jeg en hulens masse om angstanfald fra min forrige uddannelse, så imens jeg mærkede det skylle ind over mig, formåede jeg at gå ind på google og trykke "tegn på panikanfald". imens anfaldet tog til i styrke kunne jeg så sidde og følge med på listen på min computer.

åndedrætsbesvær, tjek,
kvælningsfornemmelse, tjek,
hjertebanken, tjek, osv. osv.

selvom jeg godt var klar over, hvad der skete med mig og derfor også godt vidste, at det ikke var farligt, var det møg ubehageligt. jeg var lammet og jeg spekulerede da også på, om jeg måske alligevel var ved at dø. da jeg endelig begyndte at komme ned i min krop igen, fik jeg også møflet mig gennem lokalet og udenfor døren, så jeg kunne sidde alene og komme helt til mig selv. da det var stilnet af, følte jeg mig ikke længere som mig selv og jeg var så udmattet at jeg gik direkte ind, pakkede mine ting, tog hjem og sov helt til næste dag.

jeg ved godt, hvad der udløste anfaldet.

hvis du har læst mit post (med orkide billedet), ved du, at jeg har været i en rigtigt grim situation med en mand, der gennem flere år har udøvet psykisk og seksuel terror på mig og en større gruppe unge kvinder. min forelæser fra dagen med mit angstanfald minder mig så meget om ham. generelt har jeg det altid dårligt, når han underviser og jeg bliver ofte nødt til at forlade hans forelæsninger. jeg er så ked af, at et andet menneske har haft så meget magt over mig, at selvom det er slut, kan han stadigvæk ødelægge min hverdag.

#angst #angstanfald #panikangst #metoo #ærligsnak #duerikkealene #sårbardeling #deterokayikkeatværeokay

text:
“you are flesh and bones and emotions, held together by water molecules and vibrations. 💧⁣ ⁣ 
you are not your diagnosis,⁣ you are not your pain,⁣ you are not your experiences.⁣ ⁣ 
you are the mashup of your reactions to these things.⁣ ⁣ 
you are a series of imbalances. 🌚🌝⁣ ⁣ 
but that’s what makes you alive- the imbalance dynamic causes us to bounce off each other in space, in movement, constantly.💥⁣ ⁣ 
this is simple physics: the consistent attempt of the universe to come back together in balance.⁣ ⁣ 
and as we descend into the float tank of experiencing safe touch… as the body begins to understand what safety is, the mind fragments.✨⁣ ⁣ 
our stories float to the surface, and we realize that we don’t need to carry all the things with us… 📖⁣ ⁣ 
and we come to understand that acknowledging ownership and letting go of our stories is the path to freedom.🕊”
.
beautiful words shared from @sacral_spaces via @wellsetco
.

text: i'd like to explain something to those who have not experienced the effects of childhood abuse. as we survivors grow older, all of the feelings and beliefs we had about ourselves during our abuse do not just go away when we become knowledgeable or gain awareness, or even when our life changes because of something new and exciting. they stay deep within our minds and in our hearts until we go in there and set them free. the effects that we suffered through during our teens and adulthood were felt and suffered through by all of those around us. some evil things too. but i'd like to say that the cause of those effects is by far much much more evil, yet it is the effects that are most talked about and vilified. i don't talk about it much but i suffer from ptsd and it's a daily struggle to live with it. it's far from over because there are still years of my childhood still hidden away in the darkest corners of my mind. i know that they must come to the light because just like with the other memories that came to light, it explained why i had been suffering certain effects throughout my life. my point is......the effects that we as victims of child abuse suffered were very bad yes.... and they need to be dealt with but...we as a society need to get to the root of the problem. stop the child abuse! victim to victor - #metoo #mentoo #solaceinchaos #childhoodsexualabusesurvivor #losangeles #atlanta #neworleans #philadelphia #chicago #book #film #writer #podcast @20thcenturyfox @nbc @hbo @showtime @lifetimemovies @ladygaga @terrycrews #london #australia

text:
i just want to sleep. a coma would be nice. or amnesia. anything, just to get rid of this, these thoughts, whispers in my mind. flashbacks. the terrifying feeling that it’s happening over and over again, for what feels like the first time. 
it’s hard to be optimistic for a finish line that keeps moving. 
however, you are not what has happened to you, you are how you overcome it. 
take things step by step, day by day and strive for a better yesterday. 
the worst has been and the best is yet to come, if only you have the courage to take the first step in pursing your dreams.

text:
🦋 it’s weird to see old photos of myself. 
knowing i was a completely different person then as i am now. both physically and emotionally.
it’s weird to realise that we both knew different worlds and lead completely different lives. 
one trusted easily and the other simply does not anymore. 
one had her whole life mapped out in front of her while the other barely makes it through the day 🦋
to anyone who has been through the same thing as me. 
a word of advice: 
these people have taken enough from you; your time, your body, your mind and most importantly your worth. 
do not give them anything more. 
you are the same person. you are beautiful, strong and you are loved. 
you are the same person only stronger, smarter and more determined then every to conquer the world! whatever that may be to any individual. 
even if you feel alone, do not throw yourself away. 
fight for what you lost because unlike others, you will thrive. and conquer everything and anything that gets in the way of your goals and dreams. 
and because you’ve seen the darkest parts of world world and survived.
anything is possible. 
if only you believe ✨

text:
a little compilation to show much respect to nike for the upcoming women’s history month and their show of support for it. .
.
those that know me know i love my guys dearly. and for as much as you guys push the boundaries of other men’s discomfort on mine and many other women’s behalves, because true respect for humble hard work combined with kick ass effort and dedication to making everyone better exists in your world,  know that there are those that will never see eye to eye with your support. .
.
and regardless that it falls on deaf ears, brains, leadership, etc...know that your continued “give” in this equality matters. .
.
so thank you to the men i have known, worked with, worked beside, helped, have helped me, and continue to drive forward in just kick ass “do work” mode.
.
.
and to the women, i have known, worked with, worked beside, helped, have helped me, and also continue to drive forward in the same kick ass “do work” mode....thank you.  thank you for the kick ass. thank you for the bravery it takes to walk that line, sometimes alone.  thank you for not being afraid to stand alone to make it better for others. thank you for being true to you.  not because you want something for it. not because you are looking for a damn thing. but for doing it...because it is just you...in your fierce, woman, warrior, kick-ass, way.  your humble hard work speaks for itself!  never stop your give in this endeavor....because in your own way....it moves mountains whether you know it or not.
.
.

#dowork
.
.

text:
it can be so easy for us to listen to the fear of our traumas. sometimes it even makes sense to listen to them because they are so good at convincing us something isn't right just because it creates a certain emotional reaction in us. 
more often than not though these fears keep us small, locked in our comfort zone and so the life that we dream can never be achieved because that life we dream of exists outside of the comfort zone.

text:
🌻childhood sexual abuse🌻
.
i am a survivor of csa
.
i was sexually abused by a family friend when i was very young. around four or five, i don’t remember the age. but i remember it all. it will never leave me
.
i was told to never tell my parents. and i didn’t, for over ten years. i lived with a pervasive sense of “wrongness”, boundarilessness and deep shame my whole childhood. i wanted to tell, but was terrified that i would be found out as a horrible girl, that i would be rejected and that this is what i deserved.

i revealed it to a boyfriend in my teens. we had a very deep unhealthy relationship and he was violent. as an abusive revenge tactic, after physically assaulting me, he told all my friends at school about it
.
they all said i was making it up for attention
.
i told my parents. it was reported to police. the police told my parents that there would not be enough evidence to prove him guilty in court because i was too young. the police also warned that i would be cross examined and have to tell my story in court in front of strangers; would i be comfortable with this? i opted out.
.
i have had layers of trauma in my life but this laid the foundation for the others to cut even deeper
.
this also laid the foundation for me to be abused and manipulated by more people in my life
.
i don’t know where my abuser is, if he is alive, and i shudder to think that because i didn’t have a voice to bring forth truth, that he has, and maybe even continues to hurt others
.
i share this off the back of some recent news in australia of cardinal george pell being convicted of childhood sexual abuse in the catholic church
.
for too long the voices of csa survivors have been locked up in the dark, and i want others to know that if you experienced this, you are not alone. you are not a shameful person. you are a beautiful innocent soul and what happened to you was wrong and horrible and there is hope for your restoration
.
i’m proud to see people like my friend @metoowhatnow sharing his story and getting this incredibly common and devastating reality out into open public discussion
.
may the future be open to vulnerability. may we believe survivors 
#metoo

text:
today was rough. i broke out all my go to feel good things. heck, i even meditated tonight (which, ps, i really need to get back into).
-
after reading a very long winded, victim blame filled email, i found myself spiralling back into old thought processes. i was so triggered my head was spinning.
-
i found myself wondering if my past is my fault. maybe i should’ve been more obvious with my cries for help. maybe i should’ve told more people. maybe i shouldn’t have tried to normalize and push down everything that happened to me. maybe i shouldn’t have tried to accept it and move on like it never happened.
-
also, i was a child. i was doing what i thought best to survive. i was doing everything i could to preserve my sense of self.
-
i 👏🏻 am 👏🏻 not 👏🏻 to 👏🏻 blame 👏🏻 for 👏🏻 what 👏🏻 happened 👏🏻 to 👏🏻 me 👏🏻
perhaps a little louder for those in the back. i am not responsible for other people’s actions. i will not feel guilty. i will not take the blame. not this time. i’m a little older and a little wiser and a hell of a lot stronger.
-
to all the victim blamers out there, go fuck yourself. 🖐🏻🎤 .
.
.
#complecptsd #sexualassault #metoo #welcometomyjourney #victimblaming #itsnotyourfault #thankgodfortherapy

text:
desde los 12 años empecé a sufrir acosos callejeros, desde guarangadas hasta manoseos. la primera vez estaba sentada en una plaza, paró un remis, el remisero bajó los vidrios y empezó a masturbarse mirándome, cuando llegué a mi casa me largué a llorar, pero jamás le conté a nadie.
nunca iba a imaginarme que mientras pasaba el tiempo, debía acostumbrarme a éstos actos violentos.
cuando tenía aproximadamente 15 años, subí al bondi, me senté y alado mío se sentó un señor que sacó su miembro a fuera y empezó a masturbarse (otra vez), me levanté rápidamente y bajé del colectivo. no se lo conté a nadie.
en plena adolescencia era una cosa de todos los días escuchar a esos tipos gritarme cosas inapropiadas, era normal que de vez en cuando algún enfermo de éstos me siguiera, y yo buscando desesperadamente un lugar donde esconderme.
a los 19 años, a unas cuadras de casa, dos hombres se bajaron de un auto, uno de ellos me amenazó con un arma, le dije con mucho miedo, "tomá mi celular, es todo lo que tengo, por favor no tengo más nada". la respuesta fue "callate hija de puta, no queremos eso, gritás y morís acá, así que veni y subite al auto calladita". pero no, me resistí y grité sin dudar, prefería arriesgarme, total lo que tenían pensado hacer conmigo iba a matarme igual. grité con toda mi fuerza, finalmente recibí una trompada en la cara que me tiró al piso y ahí quedé sentada llorando, sin entender por qué. pero no denuncié... para qué?...
desde jefes, profesores, compañeros, desde personas que parecen "normales", ésto se fue repitiendo. hoy gracias a la lucha de éstas mujeres valientes, ésto disminuyó.
y cuando veo en la calle algún desequilibrado intentando molestar a otras yo me meto, yo intercedo, porque estoy harta, porque me cansé. porque merecemos estar tranquilas en algún momento. porque hay personas tan enfermas que cuestionan a la víctima. 
todos los días al llegar a casa agradezco, porque "llegué bien", nadie me hizo nada ésta vez, "hoy tuve suerte".
ésto va a cambiar, porque entre nosotras nos apoyamos, ellos van a caer. todos éstos psicópatas que andan arruinando vidas. van a caer.
fuerza mujeres. no nos callan más.

text:
dear you,

there are times in life when taking a risk is better left for another day. other times are perfect for taking that leap, no matter how dangerous it might seem. well, hold on to your parachute strings - for today is leap time! realize that no matter what, we will not let you fall down, drown, get lost, or hurt yourself in any way on this one. even if it may feel like you are in free fall, we are here for you, and you can stop freaking out about getting hurt and relax into this transition to something new. 
all the elements are in place and your soul is ready for a new experience. no matter what you are asking about, it is time to take that risk and do that thing that scares you. no matter what happens, you will land softly, right on target. don’t worry about the outcome - spirits got that covered. 
it’s taking the leap itself that’s the point. 
we love your courage! 
embrace it! - postcards from spirit

text:
this is your life, and you are the writer. the author of your story. the creator of your experiences. you and only you are here to determine what gets written onto that page. even with there being several billion pages being written simultaneously, there is not a single one that even remotely matches your own. the sacredness and beauty of your story exist regardless of how many others there may be. and it's all up to you how you design it. 
this is your life. you are the creator. the artist. you decide.

text:
i am so excited to hold our brand new book in my hands. you’ve got this mama too.

text:
day 56: 9 to 5...
mariah: for the 1980s, 9 to 5 was definitely revolutionary and the seeds of that frustration would spill over to where we’re at now with #metoo and #timesup. the film is so resonant there’s talks of a sequel as sexual discrimination and harassment continue to plague our workplaces. a film that is humorous, biting, and demonstrates a future we hopefully are getting to in terms of equal pay, daycare, and overall better work conditions. jane fonda, lily tomlin, and dolly parton are a dream and their willingness to call out gender inequality is not to be forgotten ❤️...
yasmin: what a time-warp treat. though produced in 1980, it’s incredible how timely a film about inequality and sexism fits right into our modern day. we follow three women who fantasize about taking down their machismo boss, but a marijuana-induced fugue quickly becomes reality in this vintage satire. we still live in a world built for men by people of color and womxn, but it was incredible to see the dreams of flexible hours, in-house daycare, equal pay, and personalized work spaces. this is a film quite revolutionary for its time and we would gain so much by manifesting the world we deserve.

#chicagotheatretriathlon #9to5life #9to5 #9to5film #dollyparton #janefonda #lilytomlin #screentostage #9to5musical

text:
худеете в тренажёрном зале? 🏋️‍♂️ ученые из бразилии и великобритании утверждают, что максимальная потеря веса происходит при так называемых интервальных тренировках, а не во время длительных нагрузок 🏃‍♀️.
.
портал business insider приводит слова автора исследования пауло джентиль: «похудение зависит не только от того, сколько калорий вы сжигаете во время тренировки, но также и от процессов, происходящих в вашем теле после...»
.
после интервальных тренировок похудение продолжается еще несколько часов за счёт того, что при интенсивной нагрузке больше обычного истощается кислород и энергетические вещества в тканях, в результате организм продолжает активно расщеплять жировые отложения, чтобы получить необходимую энергию и после завершения тренировки.

но #интервальные тренировки подходят не всем! это, например, интенсивные беговые спринты, прыжки из глубокого приседа, #берпи (сочетание прыжка, планки и отжимания). подобные упражнения способствуют быстрому истощению кислорода, доступного мышцам, но требуют хорошей физической формы и ⚠️ опасны при многих болезнях...
.
✔️ #visiotuning тоже вызывает длительное последействие в вашем организме, но абсолютно безопасен и даже полезен! @visiotuning поможет вам не просто похудеть, а закрепить достигнутые результаты надолго! пишите заявку на бесплатную консультацию в  direct или в мессенджеры!

text:
breakthrough. last week during my session, my therapist interrupted me and said, firmly, “stop thinking for other people.” it’s easier said than done, of course. and i know that anxiety disorder is rooted in overthinking *everything* (and hashing out every possible scenario that hasn’t even happened yet). but no one had ever explained it to me in these terms. if anxiety is a shroud that has been unceremoniously draped over my head, the cloth is a least clean now, and i can see some light shining through in places where there was only matted darkness before. •
i know that this habit was borne of the abuse i’ve been through. it’s a coping mechanism i’ve used to keep myself safe. “never allow yourself to get into vulnerable situations -> never be vulnerable -> never get hurt again!” not so much. i have held myself back from so much potential joy through the years simply because i’ve assumed the worst before it’s even happened. i’ve made decisions based solely on unfavorable  imaginary conversations that have only taken place within my mind. we all do this to an extent (judgement), but i was doing it to an unhealthy degree. vulnerability doesn’t work that way. being an intelligent woman, i’m sure i’d claim to know that if someone spelled it out for me. and yet… the subconscious is a motherf*¢&^r.  but now that i’ve named- now that i’ve called it on it’s bullish!t- it’s possible for me to catch and correct myself when i do it. 2019 is all about replacing old, unhealthy coping mechanisms with healthy new ones! ✨🌱#anxiety #anxietydisorder #gad #therapy #mentalhealthawareness #mentalillness #mentalwellness #selflove #selfcare #survivor #survivoradvocate #believesurvivors #believewomen #believeblackwomen #rapesurvivor #sexualabuse #childhoodsexualabuse #csasurvivor#metoo #timesup #endrapeculture #metoomovement

repost by surviving_a_narc:  i was supposed to have the weekend “off” for my friend’s bachelorette party, but got the flu instead. sometimes shit just happens. anyway, the few times i did see my friends, my husband made himself very useful and was being very generous and kind to everyone and of course, treating me like a queen in front of them all. well today everyone left and i’m feeling a little better so i decided to have brunch with them before they took off for the airport. he attempted to sabotage that by saying we “needed to talk about today’s plans” and my mother, who was in town to watch the kids, recognized what he was doing so she said, “i just ordered you an uber and it will be here in 4 minutes.” he was pissed. i took off and he proceeded to stand in the driveway looking at me like i was getting into my lover’s car—very angry. and then the texts started...”i deserve a fucking award” (for doing the things he volunteered for) and that my “words are very hurtful” (?). he was just mad that i was having brunch with my friends 🤷🏻‍♀️ anyway, time for the other him to re-emerge. all of the girls are gone so he’s back to being himself, whoever that is. •
•
•
•
•
•
•
•
•
•

be your own cheerleader and scream from the roof tops that you have no limits to what you can do.

text:
still in the hospital, but i have my phone back so i might post about the experience, might not. the important thing is that it’s not as scary as it seems and if any of y’all are in a crisis or thinking about ending it all then i really do encourage you to reach out to someone, call 911, or have a friend take you to the er where you can be admitted into a psych unit. it’s really nice here and if you are wanting to kill yourself, what do you have to lose by giving the hospital a shot? my dm’s are always open if anyone wants to know more about hospitalization or anything else ❤️

________________________________________порой не ценим, что имеем,всю жизнь торопимся куда-то.всё кажется, что не успеем,а жизнь прошла, ей нет возврата.уже и дочки наши - мамы,и папы с мамой нет в живых...остались в памяти усталойих лики, милых и родных.подходишь к зеркалу в надежде,что ты всё так же молода,и видишь, что такой, как преждеуже не будешь никогда.и красота куда-то делась,и злых морщин не победить,и юность, как бы не хотелось,увы, уже не воскресить.бежим по жизни, как шальные,не замечая лет своих.бежим по жизни, как чумные,забыв про близких и родных.когда-нибудь и наши детипоймут в коварной суете -ничто не вечно на планете...что и они уже не те...не торопитесь! не спешите!цените каждый день и час!всё просто - радуйтесь, живитеникак не завтра, а сейчас!стихи.ру

text:
in college i would sit and read sufi poetry, while sitting in dunn brothers coffee, smoking clove cigarettes and indignantly talk with my friends about significant things like, “society as a whole”, solving the worlds’ problems and aching for the love the sufis wrote about. 
i didn’t know what the eternal beloved was, but knew i wanted that love. 
that profound love? that’s with ourselves.  and with god. 
maya angelou wrote, “a woman’s heart must be so hidden in god that a man has to seek him to find her”. ready to find that depth?
